title: Presidential Election
subtitle: The presidential term has ended
new-page: true
view-if: (year = next_presidential_election_year and month >= next_presidential_election_month) or (year > next_presidential_election_year)
on-arrival: presidential_election_active = 1; round = 0; last_presidential_election = year; hindenburg_running = 1 if not hindenburg_dead; hindenburg_running = 0 if hindenburg_dead
max-visits: 999
tags: event
face-image: img/reichstag_2.jpg

= Presidential Election

[? if president : The term of President [+ president +] has ended. ?][? if not president : Germany requires a new president. ?]

Presidential elections will be held. If no candidate receives a majority in the first round, the top two candidates will advance to a runoff election.

All major parties are preparing their candidates for the race.

- @party_candidates: Who are the candidates?

@party_candidates
on-arrival: {! Q.tactical_summary = ""; !}

The Social Democrats must settle on their own candidate and strategy before anyone else in the Reichstag commits to theirs.

**SPD:**

We must choose our candidate and strategy.

- @spd_candidate_menu: Choose our candidate.

@spd_candidate_menu

Who should represent the SPD in this election?

- @eckener_r1: Propose Hugo Eckener as a unity candidate for the Weimar Coalition.
- @adenauer_r1: Support the Center Party's candidate. ([+ z_default_candidate +])
- @gessler_r1: Support an independent liberal candidate - Gessler.
- @stresemann_r1: Support Gustav Stresemann (if alive and DVP amenable).
- @hindenburg_r1
- @westarp_r1: Support Kuno von Westarp (if DNVP line 1 - moderate).
- @schaffer_r1: Support Franz Schäffer (BVP).
- @drewitz_r1: Support Max Drewitz (WP - Economic Party).
- @hamkens_r1: Support the CNBL candidate (agrarian interests).
- @rosenfeld_r1: Support Kurt Rosenfeld (SAPD - if formed).
- @horsing_r1: Support Otto Hörsing (SRPD - if formed).
- @thalmann_r1: Support the KPD candidate (if relations are good).
- @munzenberg_r1: Support the KPD candidate (if relations are good).
- @noske_r1: Support the Gustav Noske, crusher of communist revolution.
- @braun_r1: Nominate Otto Braun.
- @schumacher_r1: Nominate Kurt Schumacher.
- @schmid_r1: Nominate Carlo Schmid.
- @ollenhauer_r1: Nominate Erich Ollenhauer.
- @juchacz_r1: Nominate Marie Juchacz.
- @cultural_figure: Nominate a nonpartisan cultural figure.
- @abstain_r1: Don't field a candidate, see who emerges.

@noske_r1
subtitle: Your way.
view-if: april_challenge = 1
choose-if: left_strength < reformist_strength + center_strength + labor_strength + neorevisionist_strength
unavailable-subtitle: Your party is leftist. No?
on-arrival: spd_candidate = "Noske"; is_unity_candidate = 1
go-to: resolve_ai_candidates

We have put forward Gustav Noske, the exterminator of communists. He is unexpectedly appealing for right wingers. Not for leftists?

@hindenburg_r1
title: Support Paul von Hindenburg - the field marshal as unity candidate
view-if: hindenburg_running = 1
choose-if: reformist_strength >= left_strength or neorevisionist_strength >= 30
unavailable-subtitle: [? if reformist_strength < left_strength and neorevisionist_strength < 30 : The left wing blocks this. ?]
on-arrival: spd_candidate = "Hindenburg"; is_unity_candidate = 1; left_dissent += 8; labor_dissent += 5; dnvp_relation += 5; z_relation += 8; dvp_relation += 8; ddp_relation += 8;
go-to: resolve_ai_candidates

We will support Field Marshal von Hindenburg, who has broad support across democratic parties.

@drewitz_r1
subtitle: Support the middle-class economic candidate - unusual coalition.
view-if: wp_candidate and (wp_candidate = "Drewitz" or wp_default_candidate = "Drewitz")
choose-if: (reformist_strength >= 35 or neorevisionist_strength >= 35) and wp_relation >= 45
unavailable-subtitle: [? if reformist_strength < 35 and neorevisionist_strength < 35 : The party left wing blocks this. ?][? if wp_relation < 45 : WP relations not good enough. ?]
on-arrival: spd_candidate = "Drewitz"; wp_relation += 8; ddp_relation += 4; dvp_relation += 3; left_dissent += 12; labor_dissent += 8; workers_spd -= 3; old_middle_spd += 3; new_middle_spd += 2; is_unity_candidate = 1;
go-to: resolve_ai_candidates

We will support Max Drewitz of the Economic Party (WP). This is a bold attempt to win middle-class voters and build a broad anti-extremist coalition.

This will anger our left wing and trade unions.

@hamkens_r1
subtitle: Support the agrarian candidate - extraordinary rural outreach.
view-if: cnbl_candidate and (cnbl_candidate = "Hamkens" or cnbl_candidate = "Behrens")
choose-if: (reformist_strength >= 45 or neorevisionist_strength >= 40) and cnbl_relation >= 50 and (agricultural_finance >= 2 or state_buyer = 1)
unavailable-subtitle: [? if reformist_strength < 45 and neorevisionist_strength < 40 : The party left wing blocks this. ?][? if cnbl_relation < 50 : CNBL relations not good enough. ?][? if not agricultural_policy_seen : We haven't engaged enough with agricultural policy. ?]
on-arrival: spd_candidate = cnbl_candidate; cnbl_relation += 10; bvp_relation += 4; z_relation += 2; left_dissent += 15; labor_dissent += 10; center_dissent += 5; workers_spd -= 4; rural_spd += 4; old_middle_spd += 2; is_unity_candidate = 1;
go-to: resolve_ai_candidates

We will support [+ cnbl_candidate +] of the CNBL. This unprecedented move signals our commitment to representing rural Germany alongside workers.

This causes major dissent across the party, especially among urban workers and the left.

@rosenfeld_r1
subtitle: Support the SAPD candidate - healing the socialist split.
view-if: sapd_formed = 1
choose-if: sapd_relation >= 50 and (left_strength >= 35 or neorevisionist_strength >= 30)
unavailable-subtitle: [? if spd_sapd_relation < 50 : Relations with SAPD not good enough. ?][? if left_strength < 35 and neorevisionist_strength < 30 : Party won't accept supporting the splitters. ?]
on-arrival: spd_candidate = "Rosenfeld"; spd_sapd_relation += 10; left_strength += 3; reformist_dissent += 8; labor_dissent += 5; is_unity_candidate = 0;
go-to: resolve_ai_candidates

We will support Kurt Rosenfeld of the SAPD. This is a step toward healing the socialist split and reunifying the workers' movement.

[? if spd_sapd_relation >= 65 : This could lead to eventual reunification... ?]

@horsing_r1
subtitle: Support the SRPD candidate - bringing back the social republicans.
view-if: srpd_formed = 1
choose-if: srpd_relation >= 50 and (reformist_strength >= 35 or neorevisionist_strength >= 30)
unavailable-subtitle: [? if srpd_relation < 50 : Relations with SRPD not good enough. ?][? if reformist_strength < 35 and neorevisionist_strength < 30 : Not enough support in party. ?]
on-arrival: spd_candidate = "Horsing"; srpd_relation += 10; reformist_strength += 2; neorevisionist_strength += 2; left_dissent += 5; is_unity_candidate = 1;
go-to: resolve_ai_candidates

We will support Otto Hörsing of the SRPD. The social republicans have proven their commitment to the Republic, and this gesture may bring them back to the fold.

[? if srpd_relation >= 70 : Hörsing has indicated he would rejoin the SPD if elected... ?]

@stresemann_r1
subtitle: Support the great statesman of the Republic.
view-if: stresemann_dead = 0 and year <= 1929 and dvp_relation >= 40
choose-if: dvp_relation >= 40
unavailable-subtitle: DVP relations not good enough.
on-arrival: spd_candidate = "Stresemann"; dvp_relation += 8; ddp_relation += 6; z_relation += 4; is_unity_candidate = 1; left_dissent += 3;
go-to: resolve_ai_candidates

We will support Gustav Stresemann, Germany's greatest democratic statesman. This is a powerful symbol of republican unity.

@westarp_r1
subtitle: Support the moderate conservative - an extraordinary anti-extremist coalition.
view-if: dnvp_line = 1 and (nsdap_r >= 15 or kpd_r >= 10) and dnvp_relation >= 10
choose-if: reformist_strength >= 40 or neorevisionist_strength >= 35
unavailable-subtitle: [? if reformist_strength < 40 and neorevisionist_strength < 35 : The party left wing blocks this. ?]
on-arrival: spd_candidate = "Westarp"; dnvp_relation += 10; z_relation += 8; dvp_relation += 6; left_dissent += 15; labor_dissent += 8; workers_spd -= 4; unemployed_spd -= 3; new_middle_spd += 2; old_middle_spd += 3; is_unity_candidate = 1;
go-to: resolve_ai_candidates

In these desperate times, we will support Kuno von Westarp of the moderate DNVP. This is an unprecedented anti-extremist front spanning from socialists to conservatives.

This will cause major dissent in our left wing.

@schaffer_r1
subtitle: Support the Bavarian conservative - pragmatic coalition-building.
view-if: bvp_relation >= 40 and z_relation >= 40
choose-if: reformist_strength >= 35 or neorevisionist_strength >= 30
unavailable-subtitle: [? if reformist_strength < 35 and neorevisionist_strength < 30 : The party left wing blocks this. ?]
on-arrival: spd_candidate = "Schäffer"; bvp_relation += 8; z_relation += 5; catholics_spd -= 2 if catholics_spd < 15; left_dissent += 10; labor_dissent += 5; is_unity_candidate = 1;
go-to: resolve_ai_candidates

We will support Franz Schäffer of the BVP. While conservative, he is a committed republican and acceptable coalition partner.

@abstain_r1
subtitle: Don't nominate anyone yet - see how the field develops.
view-if: resources >= 3
choose-if: resources >= 1
unavailable-subtitle: We need at least 1 resource to pursue this strategy.
on-arrival: spd_candidate = null; resources -= 1; spd_delayed_choice = 1;

We will wait to see which candidates emerge before committing our support. This gives us maximum flexibility.

Other parties have announced their candidates. Now we must choose.

- @spd_late_choice: Choose our candidate now.

@spd_late_choice

The field is now clear. Who should we support?

**Available Candidates:**

[? if z_candidate : - *[+ z_candidate +]* (Center) <br> ?]

[? if bvp_candidate and bvp_candidate != z_candidate : - *[+ bvp_candidate +]* (BVP) <br> ?]

[? if dvp_candidate : - *[+ dvp_candidate +]* (DVP) <br> ?]

[? if ddp_candidate : - *[+ ddp_candidate +]* (DDP) <br> ?]

[? if dsbp_candidate : - *[+ dsbp_candidate +]* (DSBP) <br> ?]

[? if dnvp_candidate and dnvp_line = 1 : - *[+ dnvp_candidate +]* (DNVP) <br> ?]

[? if kpd_candidate : - *[+ kpd_candidate +]* (KPD) <br> ?]

[? if nsdap_candidate : - *[+ nsdap_candidate +]* (NSDAP) — NEVER <br> ?]

- @support_z_late: Support [+ z_candidate +]
- @support_dvp_late: Support [+ dvp_candidate +] (if DVP not supporting Z)
- @support_wp_late: Support [+ wp_candidate +] (if WP running)
- @support_cnbl_late: Support [+ cnbl_candidate +] (if CNBL running)
- @support_dnvp_late: Support [+ dnvp_candidate +] (if moderate DNVP)
- @support_kpd_late: Support [+ kpd_candidate +] (if left-wing)
- @hindenburg_r1
- @own_candidate_late: Run our own candidate after all

@support_wp_late
view-if: wp_candidate
choose-if: (reformist_strength >= 40 or neorevisionist_strength >= 35) and wp_relation >= 45
unavailable-subtitle: [? if reformist_strength < 40 and neorevisionist_strength < 35 : The left wing blocks this. ?][? if wp_relation < 45 : Relations not good enough. ?]
on-arrival: spd_candidate = wp_candidate; wp_relation += 8; left_dissent += 12; is_unity_candidate = 1;
go-to: resolve_ai_candidates

We will support [+ wp_candidate +] of the Economic Party.

@support_cnbl_late
view-if: cnbl_candidate
choose-if: (reformist_strength >= 45 or neorevisionist_strength >= 40) and cnbl_relation >= 50
unavailable-subtitle: [? if reformist_strength < 45 and neorevisionist_strength < 40 : The left wing blocks this. ?][? if cnbl_relation < 50 : Relations not good enough. ?]
on-arrival: spd_candidate = cnbl_candidate; cnbl_relation += 10; left_dissent += 15; labor_dissent += 10;
go-to: resolve_ai_candidates

We will support [+ cnbl_candidate +] of the CNBL - an extraordinary rural outreach.

@support_z_late
view-if: z_candidate
on-arrival: spd_candidate = z_candidate; z_relation += 6; is_unity_candidate = 1;
go-to: resolve_ai_candidates

We will support [+ z_candidate +].

@support_dvp_late
view-if: dvp_candidate and dvp_candidate != z_candidate
on-arrival: spd_candidate = dvp_candidate; dvp_relation += 5; is_unity_candidate = 1;
go-to: resolve_ai_candidates

We will support [+ dvp_candidate +].

@support_dnvp_late
view-if: dnvp_candidate and dnvp_line = 1
choose-if: reformist_strength >= 40 or neorevisionist_strength >= 35
on-arrival: spd_candidate = dnvp_candidate; dnvp_relation += 10; left_dissent += 15; is_unity_candidate = 1;
go-to: resolve_ai_candidates

We will support [+ dnvp_candidate +] in this extraordinary anti-extremist coalition.

@support_kpd_late
view-if: kpd_candidate
choose-if: kpd_relation >= 50 and left_strength >= 45
on-arrival: spd_candidate = kpd_candidate; kpd_relation += 5; reformist_dissent += 10;
go-to: resolve_ai_candidates

We will support [+ kpd_candidate +].

@own_candidate_late
on-arrival: resources -= 1;

We will run our own candidate after all.

- @braun_r1: Otto Braun - Prussian strongman
- @schumacher_r1: Kurt Schumacher - War hero and rising star
- @schmid_r1: Carlo Schmid - New head of the Social Democracy
- @juchacz_r1: Marie Juchacz - Historic first woman candidate

@eckener_r1
subtitle: -1 resource - A unity candidate could unite the democratic parties.
unavailable-subtitle: [? if resources < 1 : Not enough resources. ?]
choose-if: resources >= 1
on-arrival: spd_candidate = "Eckener"; is_unity_candidate = 1; resources -= 1;
go-to: resolve_ai_candidates

We have convinced Hugo Eckener, the renowned Zeppelin captain, to run as a unity candidate representing the democratic republic.

@adenauer_r1
subtitle: Supporting the Center Party candidate.
on-arrival: spd_candidate = z_default_candidate; z_relation += 4; is_unity_candidate = 1;
go-to: resolve_ai_candidates

We will support the Center Party's candidate, [+ z_default_candidate +], in the spirit of coalition unity.

@gessler_r1
subtitle: Supporting an independent liberal.
on-arrival: spd_candidate = "Gessler"; ddp_relation += 4; is_unity_candidate = 1;
go-to: resolve_ai_candidates

We will support Otto Gessler, a liberal independent who can appeal across party lines.

@thalmann_r1
view-if: kpd_candidate = "Thälmann"
choose-if: kpd_relation >= 50 and reformist_strength < left_strength
unavailable-subtitle: [? if kpd_relation < 50 : Relations with KPD not good enough. ?][? if reformist_strength >= left_strength : The reformists block this. ?]
subtitle: This will cause major dissent in the party.

Supporting Thälmann is deeply unpopular. Are we certain?

- @support_thalmann: Yes, support Thälmann.
- @spd_candidate_menu: Choose someone else.

@support_thalmann
on-arrival: spd_candidate = "Thälmann"; kpd_relation += 5; reformist_dissent += 10; center_dissent += 6; labor_dissent += 5; neorevisionist_dissent += 10; catholics_spd -= 5; new_middle_spd -= 5; old_middle_spd -= 5; rural_spd -= 5; ddp_relation -= 8; dvp_relation -= 15; z_relation -= 10; is_unity_candidate = 0;
go-to: resolve_ai_candidates

We have endorsed Ernst Thälmann of the KPD.

@munzenberg_r1
view-if: kpd_candidate = "Münzenberg"
choose-if: kpd_relation >= 40 and reformist_strength < left_strength
unavailable-subtitle: [? if kpd_relation < 40 : Relations with KPD not good enough. ?][? if reformist_strength >= left_strength : The reformists block this. ?]
subtitle: Less controversial than Thälmann, but still unpopular.
on-arrival: spd_candidate = "Münzenberg"; kpd_relation += 5; reformist_dissent += 5; ddp_relation -= 3; dvp_relation -= 5; z_relation -= 5; is_unity_candidate = 0;
go-to: resolve_ai_candidates

We have endorsed Willi Münzenberg of the KPD.

@braun_r1
subtitle: -2 resources
unavailable-subtitle: [? if resources < 2 : Not enough resources. ?][? if braun_campaign != 0 or not spd_prussia : Braun no longer wants to run. ?]
choose-if: braun_campaign = 0 and spd_prussia and resources >= 2
on-arrival: spd_candidate = "Braun"; resources -= 2; is_unity_candidate = 0;
go-to: resolve_ai_candidates

We have convinced Otto Braun to run for president.

@ollenhauer_r1
subtitle: -2 resources
unavailable-subtitle: [? if resources < 2 : Not enough resources. ?]
view-if: ideology = "left"
choose-if: ideology = "left" and resources >= 2
on-arrival: spd_candidate = "Ollenhauer"; resources -= 2; is_unity_candidate = 0;
go-to: resolve_ai_candidates

We will run the candidate from left of our party - Erich Ollenhauer.

@schmid_r1
view-if: peoples_party >= 1 and ideology != "left"
subtitle: -2 resources
choose-if: resources >= 2
unavailable-subtitle: [? if resources < 2 : Not enough resources. ?]
on-arrival: spd_candidate = "Schmid"; resources -= 2; is_unity_candidate = 0; ideology = "reformist"; z_relation += 5; ddp_relation += 5; dvp_relation += 5; bvp_relation += 5
go-to: resolve_ai_candidates

We will run the candidate from Reformist fraction - Carlo Schmid.

@schumacher_r1
subtitle: -2 resources
unavailable-subtitle: [? if resources < 2 : Not enough resources. ?]
choose-if: resources >= 2
on-arrival: spd_candidate = "Schumacher"; resources -= 2; is_unity_candidate = 0;
go-to: resolve_ai_candidates

Kurt Schumacher will be our candidate - a war hero and rising star of the party.

@juchacz_r1
subtitle: -2 resources - The first woman candidate for president!
unavailable-subtitle: [? if resources < 2 : Not enough resources. ?]
view-if: womens_rights >= 6 and family_law >= 2 and womens_work >= 2 and welfare > 0
choose-if: resources >= 2
on-arrival: spd_candidate = "Juchacz"; resources -= 2; is_unity_candidate = 0;
go-to: resolve_ai_candidates

Marie Juchacz will be our candidate - a historic moment for women's rights!

@cultural_figure
view-if: presidential_powers >= 1 and pro_republic >= 60 and pacifism >= 3
subtitle: A symbol of the new Germany...

Since presidential powers have been reduced, we could nominate a nonpartisan figure from culture or science.

- @einstein_r1: Albert Einstein, physicist.
- @mann_r1: Heinrich Mann, writer.
- @ossietzky_r1: Carl von Ossietzky, journalist.
- @spd_candidate_menu: Choose a political candidate instead.

@einstein_r1
subtitle: -2 resources
view-if: science >= 2 and kwg_research >= 1 and (major_curriculum = "scientific" or minor_curriculum = "scientific")
choose-if: resources >= 2
on-arrival: spd_candidate = "Einstein"; resources -= 2; is_unity_candidate = 0; is_cultural_candidate = 1;
go-to: resolve_ai_candidates

Albert Einstein, Nobel laureate and symbol of scientific progress, will be our candidate.

@mann_r1
subtitle: -2 resources
view-if: kpd_relation >= 50
choose-if: resources >= 2
on-arrival: spd_candidate = "Mann"; resources -= 2; is_unity_candidate = 0; is_cultural_candidate = 1;
go-to: resolve_ai_candidates

Heinrich Mann, the renowned novelist, will be our candidate.

@ossietzky_r1
subtitle: -2 resources
view-if: weltbuhne_dropped = 1
choose-if: resources >= 2
on-arrival: spd_candidate = "Ossietzky"; resources -= 2; is_unity_candidate = 0; is_cultural_candidate = 1;
go-to: resolve_ai_candidates

Carl von Ossietzky, the pacifist journalist, will be our candidate.

@resolve_ai_candidates
on-arrival: {!

// =====================================================================
// FULL SINCERE RESOLUTION ENGINE (moved here from @party_candidates).
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
// This entire engine must live in THIS block's scope, not
// @party_candidates's, because ChoiceScript scopes JS per-label and
// this is the block that actually needs to run RESOLUTION_ORDER — SPD
// has already picked by the time we get here (Q.spd_candidate is set),
// so every AI party can genuinely see and react to it from the start,
// not just the hand-picked subset the old finalize cascade covered.
// =====================================================================


// =====================================================================
// REGISTRY-DRIVEN ELECTION ENGINE
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
// Everything about "who can run, for whom, and where they sit
// ideologically" lives in three tables below: CANDIDATES, PARTIES,
// and OWN_BENCH. To add a new candidate, party, or leader
// branch, add ONE row to ONE table here. Then mirror the candidate's
// name/party/bloc in the small CAND_INFO lookup that appears in
// @finalize_candidates, @post_r1, @r2_start, and @post_r2 (those blocks
// only need display info, not resolver logic).
// =====================================================================

var CANDIDATES = {
    Hindenburg: { name: "Paul von Hindenburg", party: "I",     bloc: "center" },
    Eckener:    { name: "Hugo Eckener",        party: "Unity", bloc: "center_left" },
    Gessler:    { name: "Otto Gessler",        party: "Liberal", bloc: "center_left" },
    Einstein:   { name: "Albert Einstein",     party: "Independent", bloc: "cultural" },
    Mann:       { name: "Heinrich Mann",       party: "Independent", bloc: "cultural" },
    Ossietzky:  { name: "Carl von Ossietzky",  party: "Independent", bloc: "cultural" },
    Hitler:     { name: "Adolf Hitler",        party: "NSDAP", bloc: "far_right" },
    Goring:     { name: "Hermann Göring",      party: "NSDAP", bloc: "far_right", aliases: ["Göring"] },
    Goebbels:   { name: "Joseph Goebbels",     party: "NSDAP", bloc: "far_right" },
    Westarp:    { name: "Kuno von Westarp",       party: "DNVP", bloc: "center_right" },
    Treviranus: { name: "Gottfried Treviranus",   party: "DNVP", bloc: "center_right" },
    Lambach:    { name: "Walter Lambach",         party: "DNVP", bloc: "center_right" },
    Lindeiner:  { name: "Hans von Lindeiner-Wildau", party: "DNVP", bloc: "center_right" },
    Hugenberg:  { name: "Alfred Hugenberg",       party: "DNVP", bloc: "far_right" },
    Seldte:     { name: "Franz Seldte",           party: "DNVP/Stahlhelm", bloc: "far_right" },
    Adenauer:   { name: "Konrad Adenauer",     party: "Z", bloc: "center" },
    Kaas:       { name: "Ludwig Kaas",         party: "Z", bloc: "center" },
    Bruning:    { name: "Heinrich Brüning",    party: "Z", bloc: "center", aliases: ["Brüning"] },
    Schaffer:   { name: "Franz Schäffer",      party: "BVP", bloc: "center_right", aliases: ["Schäffer"] },
    Stresemann: { name: "Gustav Stresemann",   party: "DVP", bloc: "center_left" },
    Scholz:     { name: "Ernst Scholz",        party: "DVP", bloc: "center_right" },
    Dingeldey:  { name: "Eduard Dingeldey",    party: "DVP", bloc: "center_right" },
    Curtius:    { name: "Julius Curtius",      party: "DVP", bloc: "center" },
    Reinhold:   { name: "Peter Reinhold",      party: "DVP", bloc: "center_left" },
    Heuss:      { name: "Theodor Heuss",       party: "DDP",  bloc: "center_left" },
    Dietrich:   { name: "Hermann Dietrich",    party: "DDP",  bloc: "center_left" },
    Luders:     { name: "Hermann Lüders",      party: "DDP",  bloc: "center_left", aliases: ["Lüders"] },
    Lemmer:     { name: "Ernst Lemmer",        party: "DDP",  bloc: "center_left" },
    Mahraun:    { name: "Arthur Mahraun",      party: "DStP/Jungdo", bloc: "center_right" },
    KochWeser:  { name: "Erich Koch-Weser",    party: "DStP", bloc: "center_left", aliases: ["Koch-Weser"] },
    Maier:      { name: "Reinhold Maier",      party: "DStP", bloc: "center_left" },
    Thalmann:   { name: "Ernst Thälmann",      party: "KPD", bloc: "far_left", aliases: ["Thälmann"] },
    Munzenberg: { name: "Willi Münzenberg",    party: "KPD", bloc: "far_left", aliases: ["Münzenberg"] },
    Braun:      { name: "Otto Braun",          party: "SPD", bloc: "left" },
    Schumacher: { name: "Kurt Schumacher",     party: "SPD", bloc: "left" },
    Schmid:     { name: "Carlo Schmid",        party: "SPD (Reformist)", bloc: "center_left" },
    Ollenhauer: { name: "Erich Ollenhauer",    party: "SPD (Left)", bloc: "left" },
    Juchacz:    { name: "Marie Juchacz",       party: "SPD", bloc: "left" },
    Noske:      { name: "Gustav Noske",        party: "SPD (Right)", bloc: "center" },
    Rosenfeld:  { name: "Kurt Rosenfeld",      party: "SAPD", bloc: "far_left" },
    Horsing:    { name: "Otto Hörsing",        party: "SRPD", bloc: "center_left" },
    Hamkens:    { name: "Wilhelm Hamkens",     party: "CNBL", bloc: "center_right" },
    Behrens:    { name: "Wilhelm Behrens",     party: "CNBL", bloc: "center_right" },
    Fehr:       { name: "Anton Fehr",          party: "DBP",  bloc: "center" },
    Drewitz:    { name: "Max Drewitz",         party: "WP", bloc: "center_right" },
    Lambach2:   { name: "Walther Lambach",     party: "CSVD", bloc: "center_right" },
    Graefe:     { name: "Albrecht von Graefe", party: "DVFP", bloc: "far_right" },
    Ludendorff: { name: "Erich Ludendorff",    party: "DVFP/Völkisch", bloc: "far_right" },
    Quidde:     { name: "Ludwig Quidde",       party: "RDP",  bloc: "center_left" },
    Bohm:       { name: "Johannes Böhm",       party: "VRP",  bloc: "center_right", aliases: ["Böhm"] },
    Kunze:      { name: "Wilhelm Kunze",       party: "DTSP", bloc: "far_right" },
    HugenbergDNF: { name: "Alfred Hugenberg",       party: "DNF", bloc: "far_right" }
};

var CANDIDATE_ALIAS = {};
for (var ck in CANDIDATES) {
    CANDIDATE_ALIAS[ck] = ck;
    if (CANDIDATES[ck].aliases) {
        for (var a = 0; a < CANDIDATES[ck].aliases.length; a++) {
            CANDIDATE_ALIAS[CANDIDATES[ck].aliases[a]] = ck;
        }
    }
}

function canonEngine(name) {
    if (!name) return name;
    if (CANDIDATE_ALIAS[name]) return CANDIDATE_ALIAS[name];
    var stripped = name.normalize("NFD").replace(/[\u0300-\u036f]/g, "").replace(/_/g, "");
    return CANDIDATE_ALIAS[stripped] || stripped;
}
function candDesc(name) {
    var key = canonEngine(name);
    var c = CANDIDATES[key];
    return c ? (c.name + " (" + c.party + ")") : (name || "");
}
function candBloc(name) {
    var key = canonEngine(name);
    var c = CANDIDATES[key];
    return c ? c.bloc : "center";
}

var BLOC_ORDER = ["far_left", "left", "cultural", "center_left", "center", "center_right", "far_right"];
function blocIndex(blocName) {
    var i = BLOC_ORDER.indexOf(blocName);
    return i === -1 ? 4 : i;
}

// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
// PARTIES — display info + tier. Every party is independent: each has
// its own row in OWN_BENCH and resolves its own candidate through the
// same free-pick/finalist pipeline as every other party. No party
// inherits its pick from another party's result anymore.
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
var PARTIES = {
    spd:   { label: "SPD",  tier: "independent", requires: "Q.spd_votes > 0 && !Q.spd_banned" },
    z:     { label: "Z",    tier: "independent", requires: "Q.z_votes > 0 && !Q.z_banned" },
    dnvp:  { label: "DNVP", tier: "independent", requires: "Q.dnvp_votes > 0 && !Q.dnvp_banned" },
    dvp:   { label: "DVP",  tier: "independent", requires: "Q.dvp_votes > 0 && !Q.dvp_banned" },
    ddp:   { label: "",     tier: "independent", requires: "Q.ddp_votes > 0 && !Q.ddp_banned" },
    kpd:   { label: "KPD",  tier: "independent", requires: "Q.kpd_votes > 0 && !Q.kpd_banned" },
    nsdap: { label: "NSDAP",tier: "independent", requires: "Q.nsdap_votes > 0 && !Q.nsdap_banned" },
    bvp:   { label: "BVP",  tier: "independent", requires: "Q.bvp_votes > 0 && !Q.bvp_banned" },
    wp:    { label: "WP",   tier: "independent", requires: "Q.wp_votes > 0 && !Q.wp_banned" },
    cnbl:  { label: "CNBL", tier: "independent", requires: "Q.cnbl_votes > 0 && !Q.cnbl_banned" },
    bb:    { label: "BB",   tier: "independent", requires: "Q.bb_votes > 0 && !Q.bb_banned" },
    dhp:   { label: "DHP",  tier: "independent", requires: "Q.dhp_votes > 0 && !Q.dhp_banned" },
    csvd:  { label: "CSVD", tier: "independent", requires: "Q.csvd_votes > 0 && !Q.csvd_banned" },
    kvp:   { label: "KVP",  tier: "independent", requires: "Q.kvp_votes > 0 && !Q.kvp_banned " },
    vrp:   { label: "VRP",  tier: "independent", requires: "Q.vrp_votes > 0 && !Q.vrp_banned" },
    sapd:  { label: "SAPD", tier: "independent", requires: "Q.sapd_votes > 0 && !Q.sapd_banned" },
    srpd:  { label: "SRPD", tier: "independent", requires: "Q.srpd_votes > 0 && !Q.srpd_banned" },
    dbp:   { label: "DBP",  tier: "independent", requires: "Q.dbp_votes > 0 && !Q.dbp_banned" },
    dsbp:  { label: "DSBP", tier: "independent", requires: "Q.dsbp_votes > 0 && !Q.dsbp_banned" },
    dvfp:  { label: "DVFP", tier: "independent", requires: "Q.dvfp_votes > 0 && !Q.dvfp_banned" },
    csrp:  { label: "CSRP", tier: "independent", requires: "Q.csrp_votes > 0 && !Q.csrp_banned" },
    dnf:   { label: "DNF",  tier: "independent", requires: "Q.dnf_votes > 0 && !Q.dnf_banned" },

    kpo:   { label: "KPO",  tier: "independent", requires: "Q.kpo_votes > 0 && !Q.kpo_banned" },
    sl:    { label: "SL",   tier: "independent", requires: "Q.sl_votes > 0 && !Q.sl_banned" },
    aspd:  { label: "ASPD", tier: "independent", requires: "Q.aspd_votes > 0 && !Q.aspd_banned" },
    vnr:   { label: "VNR",  tier: "independent", requires: "Q.vnr_votes > 0 && !Q.vnr_banned" },
    hl:    { label: "HL",   tier: "independent", requires: "Q.hl_votes > 0 && !Q.hl_banned" },
    lb:    { label: "LB",   tier: "independent", requires: "Q.lb_votes > 0 && !Q.lb_banned" },
    rdp:   { label: "RDP",  tier: "independent", requires: "Q.rdp_votes > 0 && !Q.rdp_banned" },
    cvp:   { label: "CVP",  tier: "independent", requires: "Q.cvp_votes > 0 && !Q.cvp_banned" },
    sls:   { label: "SLS",  tier: "independent", requires: "Q.sls_votes > 0 && !Q.sls_banned" },
    dtsp:  { label: "DtsP", tier: "independent", requires: "Q.dtsp_votes > 0 && !Q.dtsp_banned" }
};


function partyActive(p) {
    var req = PARTIES[p].requires;
    if (!req) return true;
    try { return !!eval(req); } catch (e) { return true; }
}

// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
// GENERIC RESOLVER — walks a party's preference rows top to bottom.
// First row whose "if" is true wins; "pick" may be a literal candidate
// key or a function returning one (for cases that need to read another
// party's already-resolved candidate). A "pick" that resolves to a
// falsy value (e.g. "follow the joint ticket" when none exists) falls
// through to later rows rather than returning null early.
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
function resolveCandidate(rows) {
    for (var i = 0; i < rows.length; i++) {
        var row = rows[i];
        if (row.default !== undefined) {
            return (typeof row.default === "function") ? row.default() : row.default;
        }
        var ok;
        try { ok = !!eval(row.if); } catch (e) { ok = false; }
        if (ok) {
            var result = (typeof row.pick === "function") ? row.pick() : row.pick;
            if (result) return result;
        }
    }
    return null;
}

function jointActive() { return Q.z_dnvp_joint_possible && Q.z_dnvp_joint_candidate; }
function jointCand() { return Q.z_dnvp_joint_candidate; }
function getRelationSafe(a, b) {
    if (!Q.party_relations || !Q.party_relations[a] || !Q.party_relations[a][b]) return 0;
    return Q.party_relations[a][b];
}

// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
// ROUND 1 — FREE CANDIDATE SELECTION
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
// Each party now genuinely chooses, round to round, between fielding
// its OWN bench candidate and BACKING another party's already-resolved
// candidate — decided by the same ideology/relation scorer used in the
// round-2 runoff, rather than a hand-authored list of "if relation with
// X >= N, back X" rows per party.
//
// OWN_BENCH keeps all the narrative, state-driven logic for who a party
// WOULD run if running alone (leadership fights, hitler_dead/deported
// chains, DNVP's line 0/1/2/3, Z's Kaas/Bruning/Adenauer split, DVP's
// leader-driven positioning, etc.) — that content is specific and
// earned, not bloc math, so it stays exactly as authored.
//
// Cross-party backing is no longer hardcoded per party; instead each
// party scores its own bench candidate against every other party's
// candidate resolved so far (RESOLUTION_ORDER defines the dependency
// chain, same order as before) and pick the highest-scoring option.
// A "home bench" bonus keeps parties from reflexively defecting from a
// perfectly good candidate of their own over a marginal score delta.
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------

var BLOC_IDEO_FALLBACK_R1 = { far_left: 1, left: 2.5, cultural: 5, center_left: 4,
                               center: 5, center_right: 6.5, far_right: 9.5 };

function candIdeoScoreR1(name) {
    var key = canonEngine(name);
    var c = CANDIDATES[key];
    if (!c) return 5;
    var partyKey = (c.party || "").toLowerCase().replace(/[^a-z]/g, "");
    if (Q[partyKey + '_ideo_score'] !== undefined) return Q[partyKey + '_ideo_score'];
    return (c.bloc && BLOC_IDEO_FALLBACK_R1[c.bloc] !== undefined) ? BLOC_IDEO_FALLBACK_R1[c.bloc] : 5;
}
function vetoPenaltyR1(relation) {
    if (relation >= 15) return 0;
    return (15 - relation) * 4;
}
// HOME_BENCH_BONUS: flat score bonus for a party's own candidate, so a
// party only defects to backing someone else when that option is
// clearly better, not on a coin-flip-sized ideology/relation delta.
var HOME_BENCH_BONUS = 6;

function optionScore(votingPartyKey, candidateName, isOwnBench) {
    var fKey = canonEngine(candidateName);
    var c = CANDIDATES[fKey];
    var candPartyLabel = c ? c.party : "";
    var relation = getRelationSafe(votingPartyKey.toUpperCase(), (candPartyLabel || "").toUpperCase());
    var myIdeo = (Q[votingPartyKey + '_ideo_score'] !== undefined) ? Q[votingPartyKey + '_ideo_score'] : 5;
    var ideoGap = Math.abs(myIdeo - candIdeoScoreR1(candidateName));
    var score = -(ideoGap * 20) + (relation * 0.5) - vetoPenaltyR1(relation);
    if (isOwnBench) score += HOME_BENCH_BONUS;
    return score;
}

// Picks between a party's own bench candidate and every other already-
// resolved party's candidate. `resolvedSoFar` is the list of candidate
// names resolved earlier in RESOLUTION_ORDER (dependency chain intact,
// same as the original design — e.g. Z/BVP still wait for SPD since
// SPD resolves outside this loop, before RESOLUTION_ORDER runs).
function pickFreeCandidate(votingPartyKey, ownBenchCandidate, resolvedSoFar) {
    if (!ownBenchCandidate && (!resolvedSoFar || resolvedSoFar.length === 0)) return null;

    var best = ownBenchCandidate || null;
    var bestScore = ownBenchCandidate ? optionScore(votingPartyKey, ownBenchCandidate, true) : -Infinity;

    if (resolvedSoFar) {
        var seen = {};
        for (var i = 0; i < resolvedSoFar.length; i++) {
            var cand = resolvedSoFar[i];
            if (!cand) continue;
            var ck = canonEngine(cand);
            if (seen[ck]) continue; // don't score the same candidate twice
            seen[ck] = true;
            if (ownBenchCandidate && ck === canonEngine(ownBenchCandidate)) continue;
            var s = optionScore(votingPartyKey, cand, false);
            if (s > bestScore) { bestScore = s; best = cand; }
        }
    }
    return best;
}

// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
// OWN_BENCH — one ranked list per party (every party is independent
// now, so this covers all of them, not just the former "major" set),
// narrative/state-driven only (who they'd run if running alone). No
// cross-party fallback rows live here anymore; pickFreeCandidate()
// handles all cross-party backing generically via the scorer above.
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
var OWN_BENCH = {

    nsdap: [
        { if: "Q.hitler_dead", pick: "Goebbels" },
        { if: "Q.hitler_deported", pick: "Goring" },
        { default: "Hitler" }
    ],

    dnf: [
        { default: "Hugenberg" }
    ],

    dnvp: [
        { if: "jointActive() && Q.dnvp_line !== 3", pick: jointCand },
        { if: "Q.dnvp_line === 1", pick: "Westarp" },
        { if: "Q.dnvp_line === 2", pick: "Westarp" },
        { if: "Q.dnvp_line === 0 && Q.dnvp_party_leader === 'Westarp'", pick: "Westarp" },
        { if: "Q.dnvp_line === 0 && Q.dnvp_party_leader === 'Treviranus'", pick: "Treviranus" },
        { if: "Q.dnvp_line === 0 && Q.dnvp_party_leader === 'Lambach'", pick: "Lambach" },
        { if: "Q.dnvp_line === 0 && Q.dnvp_party_leader === 'Lindeiner-Wildau'", pick: "Lindeiner" },
        { if: "Q.dnvp_line === 0", pick: "Treviranus" },
        { if: "Q.dnvp_line === 3 && Q.nsdap_banned", pick: "Hugenberg" },
        { if: "Q.dnvp_line === 3 && Q.hitler_dead && Q.dnvp_relation_nsdap >= 70", pick: "Goebbels" },
        { if: "Q.dnvp_line === 3 && Q.hitler_dead", pick: "Hugenberg" },
        { if: "Q.dnvp_line === 3 && Q.hitler_deported", pick: "Goring" },
        { if: "Q.dnvp_line === 3", pick: "Hitler" },
        { default: "Seldte" }
    ],

    z: [
        { if: "jointActive()", pick: jointCand },
        { if: "Q.z_party_leader === 'Kaas'", pick: "Kaas" },
        { if: "Q.z_party_leader === 'Joos'", pick: "Adenauer" },
        { if: "Q.z_party_leader === 'Bruning'", pick: "Bruning" },
        { default: "Adenauer" }
    ],

    bvp: [
        { if: "jointActive()", pick: jointCand },
        { default: "Schaffer" }
    ],

    dvp: [
        { if: "!Q.stresemann_dead && Q.year <= 1929", pick: "Stresemann" },
        { if: "Q.dvp_party_leader === 'Scholz' && (Q.dvp_right_shift >= 2 || Q.capital_strike_progress >= 3) && Q.dnvp_line === 1 && Q.dnvp_relation >= 50", pick: "Westarp" },
        { if: "Q.dvp_party_leader === 'Scholz' && (Q.dvp_right_shift >= 2 || Q.capital_strike_progress >= 3)", pick: "Scholz" },
        { if: "Q.dvp_party_leader === 'Scholz'", pick: "Gessler" },
        { if: "Q.dvp_party_leader === 'Dingeldey' && Q.dvp_right_shift >= 1", pick: "Dingeldey" },
        { if: "Q.dvp_party_leader === 'Dingeldey'", pick: "Gessler" },
        { if: "Q.dvp_party_leader === 'Curtius'", pick: "Curtius" },
        { if: "Q.finance_minister === 'Reinhold' && Q.economic_policy_seen", pick: "Reinhold" },
        { default: "Gessler" }
    ],

    kpd: [
        { if: "Q.kpd_party_leader === 'Conciliators'", pick: "Munzenberg" },
        { default: "Thalmann" }
    ],

    wp: [
        { default: "Drewitz" }
    ],

    cnbl: [
        { if: "Q.agricultural_finance < 2 || Q.land_reform >= 2", pick: "Hamkens" },
        { default: "Hamkens" }
    ],

    bb: [
        { default: "Hamkens" }
    ],

    dhp: [
        { default: "Hamkens" }
    ],

    csvd: [
        { default: "Lambach2" }
    ],

    kvp: [
        { default: "Westarp" }
    ],

    vrp: [
        { if: "Q.inflation >= 5 || Q.unemployed >= 20 || Q.economy_growth <= -3", pick: "Bohm" },
        { default: "Bohm" }
    ],

    sapd: [
        { default: "Rosenfeld" }
    ],

    srpd: [
        { default: "Horsing" }
    ],

    dvfp: [
        { if: "Q.hitler_dead && !Q.nsdap_banned", pick: "Ludendorff" },
        { if: "Q.unrest_factor >= 2.0 || Q.nationalism >= 60", pick: "Ludendorff" },
        { default: "Graefe" }
    ],

    dbp: [
        { if: "Q.inflation < 0 || Q.unemployed >= 15", pick: "Fehr" },
        { default: "Fehr" }
    ],

    dsbp: [
        { if: "Q.inflation < 0 || Q.unemployed >= 15", pick: "Gessler" },
        { default: "Gessler" }
    ],

    // CSRP has no bench of its own — it always follows Z (kept as a
    // direct rule rather than scored, since it has never fielded an
    // independent candidate in the source material).
    csrp: [
        { default: function () { return Q.z_candidate; } }
    ],

    ddp: [
        { default: function () { return ddpOwnCandidate(); } }
    ],

    // ---------------------------------------------------------------------
    // Formerly-"minor" parties — each is now fully independent and gets
    // its own bench row like every other party. Their default pick is
    // the same figure they used to simply mirror from a parent party
    // (kept as-is so their likely candidate doesn't change), but they
    // now resolve, get offered/back other parties, and finalize through
    // the normal generic pipeline rather than a hardcoded inheritance.
    // ---------------------------------------------------------------------
    kpo: [
        { default: function () { return Q.kpd_candidate || Q.kpd_default_candidate || "Thalmann"; } }
    ],

    sl: [
        { default: function () { return Q.sapd_candidate || Q.sapd_default_candidate || "Rosenfeld"; } }
    ],

    aspd: [
        { default: function () { return Q.dvp_candidate || Q.dvp_default_candidate || "Gessler"; } }
    ],

    vnr: [
        { default: function () { return Q.dvp_candidate || Q.dvp_default_candidate || "Gessler"; } }
    ],

    hl: [
        { default: function () { return Q.dhp_candidate || Q.dhp_default_candidate || "Hamkens"; } }
    ],

    lb: [
        { default: function () { return Q.kpd_candidate || Q.kpd_default_candidate || "Thalmann"; } }
    ],

    rdp: [
        { default: "Quidde" }
    ],

    cvp: [
        { default: function () { return Q.z_candidate || Q.z_default_candidate || "Adenauer"; } }
    ],

    sls: [
        { default: function () { return Q.spd_candidate || "Braun"; } }
    ],

    dtsp: [
        { default: "Kunze" }
    ]
};

function ddpOwnCandidate() {
    if (Q.ddp_name === "DStP") {
        if (Q.jungdo_strength >= 300 && Q.year >= 1930) return "Mahraun";
        if (Q.ddp_party_leader === "Koch-Weser" || !Q.ddp_party_leader) return "KochWeser";
        if (Q.ddp_party_leader === "Maier") return "Maier";
        if (Q.economic_democracy >= 2 || Q.reformist_strength >= 50) return "Luders";
        return "KochWeser";
    }
    if (Q.womens_rights >= 4 && Q.pro_republic > 80 && Q.nationalism < 20) return "Luders";
    if (Q.ddp_party_leader === "Dietrich" || Q.finance_minister === "Dietrich") return "Dietrich";
    if (Q.ddp_party_leader === "Heuss") return "Heuss";
    if (Q.rb_strength >= 800 && Q.rb_militancy > 0.30 && Q.year >= 1932) return "Lemmer";
    return "Heuss";
}

// resolveCandidate (defined above) walks OWN_BENCH rows top to bottom
// to find what a party WOULD run alone (narrative rows only).

// =====================================================================
// ORCHESTRATION
// =====================================================================
Q.is_unity_candidate = 0;
Q.is_cultural_candidate = 0;

for (var ckk in CANDIDATES) {
    Q[ckk + '_bonus'] = Q[ckk + '_bonus'] || 0;
    Q[ckk + '_running'] = 0;
}

// --- Joint Z-DNVP conservative unity ticket -------------------------
Q.z_dnvp_joint_possible = 0;
Q.z_dnvp_joint_candidate = null;

if (!Q.dnvp_banned && (Q.dnvp_line === 0 || Q.dnvp_line === 1 || Q.dnvp_line === 2)) {
    var z_dnvp_rel = getRelationSafe("Z", "DNVP");
    var dnvp_z_rel = getRelationSafe("DNVP", "Z");
    var z_bvp_rel = getRelationSafe("Z", "BVP");

    if (z_dnvp_rel >= 40 && dnvp_z_rel >= 40 && z_bvp_rel >= 70) {
        if ((Q.nsdap_r >= 20 || Q.kpd_r >= 12) && Q.year >= 1930) {
            Q.z_dnvp_joint_possible = 1;
            if (Q.z_party_leader === "Kaas" && Q.dnvp_line === 0) {
                Q.z_dnvp_joint_candidate = (Q.z_r >= Q.dnvp_r) ? "Kaas" : "Westarp";
            } else if (Q.z_party_leader === "Bruning") {
                Q.z_dnvp_joint_candidate = "Bruning";
            } else if (Q.dnvp_line === 1) {
                Q.z_dnvp_joint_candidate = "Westarp";
            } else if (Q.bvp_r >= 3 && Q.z_r >= Q.dnvp_r) {
                Q.z_dnvp_joint_candidate = "Schaffer";
            } else {
                Q.z_dnvp_joint_candidate = "Adenauer";
            }
        }
    }

    Q.conservative_unity_estimate = (Q.z_r || 0) + (Q.dnvp_r || 0) + (Q.bvp_r || 0);
    if (Q.dvp_candidate === Q.z_dnvp_joint_candidate) Q.conservative_unity_estimate += (Q.dvp_r || 0);
    if (Q.wp_candidate === Q.z_dnvp_joint_candidate) Q.conservative_unity_estimate += (Q.wp_r || 0);
    if (Q.cnbl_candidate === Q.z_dnvp_joint_candidate) Q.conservative_unity_estimate += (Q.cnbl_r || 0);
    Q.conservative_unity_estimate = Math.round(Q.conservative_unity_estimate * 10) / 10;
}

// --- Resolve every party, including the formerly-"minor" ones, which
//     are now fully independent and share this same resolution pass
//     rather than waiting to mirror a parent at finalize time.
// Each party's own bench candidate comes from OWN_BENCH (narrative,
// state-driven). It then freely checks that bench candidate against
// every OTHER party's candidate resolved earlier in this same
// order — genuine cross-party backing, decided by ideology/relation
// score rather than a hardcoded "if relation >= N, back them" rule.
// SPD itself is the player's own party and isn't in this loop; parties
// that would want to back SPD get a second, final look at that once
// SPD's choice is known, in @finalize_candidates.
var RESOLUTION_ORDER = [
    "nsdap", "kpd", "dnvp", "z", "bvp", "dvp", "ddp", "wp", "cnbl",
    "bb", "dhp", "csvd", "kvp", "vrp", "sapd", "srpd", "dbp", "dsbp",
    "dvfp", "csrp", "dnf",
    "kpo", "sl", "aspd", "vnr", "hl", "lb", "rdp", "cvp", "sls", "dtsp"
];

// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
// SINCERE RESOLUTION PASS — every party (including nsdap, kpd, dnvp,
// and every other party skipped by earlier versions of this file)
// resolves its own bench vs. every already-resolved candidate,
// seeded with SPD's pick so the very first party in RESOLUTION_ORDER
// already has SPD to react to.
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
var resolvedSoFar = [Q.spd_candidate];
for (var ri = 0; ri < RESOLUTION_ORDER.length; ri++) {
    var pkey = RESOLUTION_ORDER[ri];
    if (!partyActive(pkey)) { Q[pkey + '_candidate'] = null; Q[pkey + '_default_candidate'] = null; continue; }
    var ownBench = resolveCandidate(OWN_BENCH[pkey]);
    Q[pkey + '_default_candidate'] = ownBench;
    var picked = (pkey === "csrp" || pkey === "dnf") ? ownBench : pickFreeCandidate(pkey, ownBench, resolvedSoFar);
    Q[pkey + '_candidate'] = picked;
    resolvedSoFar.push(picked);
}

// =====================================================================
// PHASE 1 OF 2 — SINCERE CANDIDATE RESOLUTION.
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
// SPD has already chosen (Q.spd_candidate is set — this block never
// runs before that). Every AI party now makes its genuine, self-
// centered choice: run its own bench candidate, or back the best-
// scoring already-resolved candidate (SPD's pick, or another party
// resolved earlier in this same sequence). This is pure ideology/
// relation math with NO awareness of projected vote totals or who is
// "winning" — that awareness is deliberately reserved for the separate
// tactical-consolidation phase (@tactical_consolidation) later, so the
// two kinds of reasoning never blend into one pass.
// =====================================================================

// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
// SHARED CANDIDATE LOOKUP (mirror of CANDIDATES in @party_candidates —
// display info only, no resolver logic needed here).
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
var CAND_INFO = {
    Hindenburg: { name: "Paul von Hindenburg", party: "I",     bloc: "center" },
    Eckener:    { name: "Hugo Eckener",        party: "Unity", bloc: "center_left" },
    Gessler:    { name: "Otto Gessler",        party: "Liberal", bloc: "center_left" },
    Einstein:   { name: "Albert Einstein",     party: "Independent", bloc: "cultural" },
    Mann:       { name: "Heinrich Mann",       party: "Independent", bloc: "cultural" },
    Ossietzky:  { name: "Carl von Ossietzky",  party: "Independent", bloc: "cultural" },
    Hitler:     { name: "Adolf Hitler",        party: "NSDAP", bloc: "far_right" },
    Goring:     { name: "Hermann Göring",      party: "NSDAP", bloc: "far_right", aliases: ["Göring"] },
    Goebbels:   { name: "Joseph Goebbels",     party: "NSDAP", bloc: "far_right" },
    Westarp:    { name: "Kuno von Westarp",       party: "DNVP", bloc: "center_right" },
    Treviranus: { name: "Gottfried Treviranus",   party: "DNVP", bloc: "center_right" },
    Lambach:    { name: "Walter Lambach",         party: "DNVP", bloc: "center_right" },
    Lindeiner:  { name: "Hans von Lindeiner-Wildau", party: "DNVP", bloc: "center_right" },
    Hugenberg:  { name: "Alfred Hugenberg",       party: "DNVP", bloc: "far_right" },
    Seldte:     { name: "Franz Seldte",           party: "DNVP/Stahlhelm", bloc: "far_right" },
    Adenauer:   { name: "Konrad Adenauer",     party: "Z", bloc: "center" },
    Kaas:       { name: "Ludwig Kaas",         party: "Z", bloc: "center" },
    Bruning:    { name: "Heinrich Brüning",    party: "Z", bloc: "center", aliases: ["Brüning"] },
    Schaffer:   { name: "Franz Schäffer",      party: "BVP", bloc: "center_right", aliases: ["Schäffer"] },
    Stresemann: { name: "Gustav Stresemann",   party: "DVP", bloc: "center_left" },
    Scholz:     { name: "Ernst Scholz",        party: "DVP", bloc: "center_right" },
    Dingeldey:  { name: "Eduard Dingeldey",    party: "DVP", bloc: "center_right" },
    Curtius:    { name: "Julius Curtius",      party: "DVP", bloc: "center" },
    Reinhold:   { name: "Peter Reinhold",      party: "DVP", bloc: "center_left" },
    Heuss:      { name: "Theodor Heuss",       party: "DDP",  bloc: "center_left" },
    Dietrich:   { name: "Hermann Dietrich",    party: "DDP",  bloc: "center_left" },
    Luders:     { name: "Hermann Lüders",      party: "DDP",  bloc: "center_left", aliases: ["Lüders"] },
    Lemmer:     { name: "Ernst Lemmer",        party: "DDP",  bloc: "center_left" },
    Mahraun:    { name: "Arthur Mahraun",      party: "DStP/Jungdo", bloc: "center_right" },
    KochWeser:  { name: "Erich Koch-Weser",    party: "DStP", bloc: "center_left", aliases: ["Koch-Weser"] },
    Maier:      { name: "Reinhold Maier",      party: "DStP", bloc: "center_left" },
    Thalmann:   { name: "Ernst Thälmann",      party: "KPD", bloc: "far_left", aliases: ["Thälmann"] },
    Munzenberg: { name: "Willi Münzenberg",    party: "KPD", bloc: "far_left", aliases: ["Münzenberg"] },
    Braun:      { name: "Otto Braun",          party: "SPD", bloc: "left" },
    Schumacher: { name: "Kurt Schumacher",     party: "SPD", bloc: "left" },
    Schmid:     { name: "Carlo Schmid",        party: "SPD (Reformist)", bloc: "center_left" },
    Ollenhauer: { name: "Erich Ollenhauer",    party: "SPD (Left)", bloc: "left" },
    Juchacz:    { name: "Marie Juchacz",       party: "SPD", bloc: "left" },
    Noske:      { name: "Gustav Noske",        party: "SPD (Right)", bloc: "center" },
    Rosenfeld:  { name: "Kurt Rosenfeld",      party: "SAPD", bloc: "far_left" },
    Horsing:    { name: "Otto Hörsing",        party: "SRPD", bloc: "center_left" },
    Hamkens:    { name: "Wilhelm Hamkens",     party: "CNBL", bloc: "center_right" },
    Behrens:    { name: "Wilhelm Behrens",     party: "CNBL", bloc: "center_right" },
    Fehr:       { name: "Anton Fehr",          party: "DBP",  bloc: "center" },
    Drewitz:    { name: "Max Drewitz",         party: "WP", bloc: "center_right" },
    Lambach2:   { name: "Walther Lambach",     party: "CSVD", bloc: "center_right" },
    Graefe:     { name: "Albrecht von Graefe", party: "DVFP", bloc: "far_right" },
    Ludendorff: { name: "Erich Ludendorff",    party: "DVFP/Völkisch", bloc: "far_right" },
    Quidde:     { name: "Ludwig Quidde",       party: "RDP",  bloc: "center_left" },
    Bohm:       { name: "Johannes Böhm",       party: "VRP",  bloc: "center_right", aliases: ["Böhm"] },
    Kunze:      { name: "Wilhelm Kunze",       party: "DTSP", bloc: "far_right" },
    HugenbergDNF: { name: "Alfred Hugenberg",       party: "DNF", bloc: "far_right" }
};
var CAND_ALIAS = {};
for (var ck0 in CAND_INFO) {
    CAND_ALIAS[ck0] = ck0;
    if (CAND_INFO[ck0].aliases) for (var a0 = 0; a0 < CAND_INFO[ck0].aliases.length; a0++) CAND_ALIAS[CAND_INFO[ck0].aliases[a0]] = ck0;
}
function canon(name) {
    if (!name) return name;
    if (CAND_ALIAS[name]) return CAND_ALIAS[name];
    var stripped = name.normalize("NFD").replace(/[\u0300-\u036f]/g, "").replace(/_/g, "");
    return CAND_ALIAS[stripped] || stripped;
}

// Hard kill: if Hindenburg is dead, zero out any stale candidate assignments
if (Q.hindenburg_dead) {
    Q.hindenburg_running = 0;
    var ALL_PARTY_KEYS = ['spd','z','dnvp','dvp','ddp','kpd','nsdap','bvp','wp','cnbl','bb','dhp','csvd','kvp','vrp','sapd','srpd','dbp','dsbp','dvfp','csrp','kpo','sl','aspd','vnr','hl','lb','rdp','cvp','sls','dtsp', 'dnf'];
    for (var i = 0; i < ALL_PARTY_KEYS.length; i++) {
        if (canon(Q[ALL_PARTY_KEYS[i] + '_candidate']) === 'Hindenburg') Q[ALL_PARTY_KEYS[i] + '_candidate'] = null;
        if (canon(Q[ALL_PARTY_KEYS[i] + '_default_candidate']) === 'Hindenburg') Q[ALL_PARTY_KEYS[i] + '_default_candidate'] = null;
    }
}

// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
// RELATION/IDEOLOGY-DRIVEN FINALIZATION — now that SPD's own choice is
// known, every other party freely re-checks whether backing SPD (or any
// other already-resolved party) scores better than running its own
// bench candidate. Same scorer as @party_candidates and the round-2
// runoff: ideology gap dominates, relation breaks ties and applies a
// soft veto below relation 15. This replaces the old per-party
// is_unity_candidate/relation-threshold cascades.
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
var BLOC_IDEO_FALLBACK_FC = { far_left: 1, left: 2.5, cultural: 5, center_left: 4,
                               center: 5, center_right: 6.5, far_right: 9.5 };
function candIdeoScoreFC(name) {
    var key = canon(name);
    var c = CAND_INFO[key];
    if (!c) return 5;
    var partyKey = (c.party || "").toLowerCase().replace(/[^a-z]/g, "");
    if (Q[partyKey + '_ideo_score'] !== undefined) return Q[partyKey + '_ideo_score'];
    return (c.bloc && BLOC_IDEO_FALLBACK_FC[c.bloc] !== undefined) ? BLOC_IDEO_FALLBACK_FC[c.bloc] : 5;
}
function vetoPenaltyFC(relation) {
    if (relation >= 15) return 0;
    return (15 - relation) * 4;
}
var HOME_BENCH_BONUS_FC = 6;
function optionScoreFC(votingPartyKey, candidateName, isOwnBench) {
    var fKey = canon(candidateName);
    var c = CAND_INFO[fKey];
    var candPartyLabel = c ? c.party : "";
    var relation = getRelationSafe(votingPartyKey.toUpperCase(), (candPartyLabel || "").toUpperCase());
    var myIdeo = (Q[votingPartyKey + '_ideo_score'] !== undefined) ? Q[votingPartyKey + '_ideo_score'] : 5;
    var ideoGap = Math.abs(myIdeo - candIdeoScoreFC(candidateName));
    var score = -(ideoGap * 20) + (relation * 0.5) - vetoPenaltyFC(relation);
    if (isOwnBench) score += HOME_BENCH_BONUS_FC;
    return score;
}
// Picks between a party's own bench candidate and a list of already-
// resolved candidates on offer (SPD's pick plus whichever other
// parties resolved earlier). Options that are banned/unavailable
// should simply be omitted from `onOffer` by the caller.
function pickFreeCandidateFC(votingPartyKey, ownBenchCandidate, onOffer) {
    var best = ownBenchCandidate || null;
    var bestScore = ownBenchCandidate ? optionScoreFC(votingPartyKey, ownBenchCandidate, true) : -Infinity;
    if (onOffer) {
        var seen = {};
        for (var i = 0; i < onOffer.length; i++) {
            var cand = onOffer[i];
            if (!cand) continue;
            var ck = canon(cand);
            if (seen[ck]) continue;
            seen[ck] = true;
            if (ownBenchCandidate && ck === canon(ownBenchCandidate)) continue;
            var s = optionScoreFC(votingPartyKey, cand, false);
            if (s > bestScore) { bestScore = s; best = cand; }
        }
    }
    return best;
}

// ========================================
// NSDAP / KPD / DNVP — these three are read by name further down
// (JOINT_LEFT, DVFP, CSVD, BB, DNF all branch on Q.nsdap_candidate,
// Q.kpd_candidate, or Q.dnvp_candidate) but have no dedicated
// hand-authored block of their own, so they must resolve FIRST, right
// here, straight off their own bench + the generic scorer (same
// pickFreeCandidate used in the pre-SPD bench precompute — SPD is
// already known by this point, so it's included in the offer list
// like every other party gets below).
// ========================================
Q.nsdap_candidate = partyActive("nsdap")
    ? pickFreeCandidate("nsdap", Q.nsdap_default_candidate, [Q.spd_candidate])
    : null;
Q.kpd_candidate = partyActive("kpd")
    ? pickFreeCandidate("kpd", Q.kpd_default_candidate, [Q.spd_candidate])
    : null;
Q.dnvp_candidate = partyActive("dnvp")
    ? pickFreeCandidate("dnvp", Q.dnvp_default_candidate, [Q.spd_candidate, Q.nsdap_candidate])
    : null;

// ========================================
// FINALIZE RESOLUTION ORDER — every party below is re-scored fresh
// against its OWN true bench default (never gated by "already set",
// since the first pass always sets *something*, which was the root
// bug for DVP/DDP). Each party's offer list includes SPD plus every
// OTHER party already finalized earlier in this exact sequence, so
// nobody compares against stale/pre-SPD values. Far-right/far-left
// anchors (DVFP) still don't get SPD in their offer — ideology gap
// makes it a non-starter and offering it risks a nonsensical result —
// but every centrist/agrarian/liberal party now gets a genuine, live
// look at SPD's pick.
//
// Joint-left short-circuit: if SPD picked the KPD candidate (unity
// left slate), every party below just keeps its own bench pick rather
// than running the scorer, matching original design intent.
// ========================================
var JOINT_LEFT = (Q.spd_candidate === Q.kpd_candidate);

// --- Z (CENTER PARTY) ---------------------------------------------
Q.z_candidate = JOINT_LEFT
    ? Q.z_default_candidate
    : pickFreeCandidateFC("z", Q.z_default_candidate, [Q.spd_candidate]);
Q.csrp_candidate = Q.z_candidate;

// --- DVP ---------------------------------------------------------------
Q.dvp_candidate = JOINT_LEFT
    ? Q.dvp_default_candidate
    : pickFreeCandidateFC("dvp", Q.dvp_default_candidate, [Q.spd_candidate, Q.z_candidate]);

// --- DDP/DStP ------------------------------------------------------------
Q.ddp_candidate = JOINT_LEFT
    ? Q.ddp_default_candidate
    : pickFreeCandidateFC("ddp", Q.ddp_default_candidate, [Q.spd_candidate, Q.z_candidate, Q.dvp_candidate]);

// --- BVP — after Z is final ---------------------------------------------
Q.bvp_candidate = JOINT_LEFT
    ? Q.bvp_default_candidate
    : pickFreeCandidateFC("bvp", Q.bvp_default_candidate,
        [Q.z_candidate, Q.spd_candidate, (!Q.dnvp_banned ? Q.dnvp_candidate : null)]);

// --- CNBL — after Z is final. Now genuinely offered SPD: CNBL is
//     agrarian center-right, not far-right, so under high relation it
//     should be able to rally behind SPD like any other centrist bloc.
if (Q.cnbl_default_candidate === "Hamkens" || Q.cnbl_default_candidate === "Behrens") {
    Q.cnbl_candidate = JOINT_LEFT
        ? Q.cnbl_default_candidate
        : pickFreeCandidateFC("cnbl", Q.cnbl_default_candidate,
            [Q.nsdap_candidate, Q.dnvp_candidate, Q.z_candidate, Q.spd_candidate]);
} else {
    Q.cnbl_candidate = Q.cnbl_default_candidate || "Hamkens";
}

// --- WP — after DVP is final --------------------------------------------
if (Q.wp_default_candidate === "Drewitz") {
    Q.wp_candidate = JOINT_LEFT
        ? Q.wp_default_candidate
        : pickFreeCandidateFC("wp", Q.wp_default_candidate, [Q.dvp_candidate, Q.spd_candidate, Q.z_candidate]);
} else {
    Q.wp_candidate = JOINT_LEFT
        ? Q.wp_default_candidate
        : pickFreeCandidateFC("wp", Q.wp_default_candidate || Q.dvp_candidate, [Q.dvp_candidate, Q.spd_candidate]);
}

// --- VRP — after DDP is final --------------------------------------------
if (Q.vrp_votes > 0) {
    var vrp_desperate = Q.inflation >= 5 || Q.unemployed >= 20 || Q.economy_growth <= -3;
    if (vrp_desperate) {
        Q.vrp_candidate = "Bohm";
    } else if (JOINT_LEFT) {
        Q.vrp_candidate = Q.vrp_default_candidate || "Bohm";
    } else {
        Q.vrp_candidate = pickFreeCandidateFC("vrp", Q.vrp_default_candidate || "Bohm",
            [Q.spd_candidate, Q.ddp_candidate]);
    }
}

// --- SAPD / SRPD -----------------------------------------------------------
if (Q.sapd_votes > 0) {
    Q.sapd_candidate = (Q.sapd_candidate === Q.kpd_candidate && JOINT_LEFT)
        ? Q.kpd_candidate
        : pickFreeCandidateFC("sapd", Q.sapd_candidate || "Rosenfeld", [Q.spd_candidate]);
}
if (Q.srpd_votes > 0) {
    Q.srpd_candidate = JOINT_LEFT
        ? (Q.srpd_default_candidate || "Horsing")
        : pickFreeCandidateFC("srpd", Q.srpd_default_candidate || "Horsing", [Q.spd_candidate]);
}

// --- KVP / DHP / BB / DBP — after Z, CNBL, BVP are final --------------------
if (Q.kvp_flee === 1 && !Q.kvp_banned) {
    if (Q.kvp_default_candidate && Q.kvp_default_candidate !== "Hitler" && Q.kvp_default_candidate !== "Hugenberg") {
        Q.kvp_candidate = JOINT_LEFT
            ? Q.kvp_default_candidate
            : pickFreeCandidateFC("kvp", Q.kvp_default_candidate, [Q.z_candidate, Q.spd_candidate]);
    } else {
        Q.kvp_candidate = Q.z_candidate || "Westarp";
    }
}

if (!Q.dhp_banned) {
    Q.dhp_candidate = JOINT_LEFT
        ? (Q.dhp_default_candidate || "Hamkens")
        : pickFreeCandidateFC("dhp", Q.dhp_default_candidate || "Hamkens", [Q.cnbl_candidate, Q.spd_candidate]);
}

if (!Q.bb_banned) {
    var bb_crisis = Q.inflation < 0 || Q.unemployed >= 15;
    if (bb_crisis) {
        Q.bb_candidate = "Hamkens";
    } else if (JOINT_LEFT) {
        Q.bb_candidate = Q.bvp_candidate || Q.cnbl_candidate || "Hamkens";
    } else {
        Q.bb_candidate = pickFreeCandidateFC("bb", Q.bb_default_candidate || "Hamkens",
            [Q.bvp_candidate, Q.z_candidate, Q.spd_candidate]);
    }
}

if (Q.dbp_votes > 0 && !Q.dbp_banned) {
    var dbp_crisis = Q.inflation < 0 || Q.unemployed >= 15;
    if (dbp_crisis) {
        Q.dbp_candidate = "Fehr";
    } else if (JOINT_LEFT) {
        Q.dbp_candidate = (Q.bb_candidate && Q.bb_candidate !== Q.kpd_candidate) ? Q.bb_candidate : (Q.cnbl_candidate || Q.ddp_candidate || "Fehr");
    } else {
        Q.dbp_candidate = pickFreeCandidateFC("dbp", Q.dbp_default_candidate || "Fehr",
            [Q.bb_candidate, Q.ddp_candidate, Q.spd_candidate]);
    }
}

// --- DVFP — far-right anchor. Deliberately NOT offered SPD: the
//     ideology gap makes it a non-starter, and offering it would let a
//     scoring edge case produce an absurd DVFP-backs-SPD result. Kept
//     exactly as original design intended.
if (Q.dvfp_banned) {
    Q.dvfp_candidate = null;
} else if (JOINT_LEFT) {
    Q.dvfp_candidate = Q.dvfp_default_candidate || "Ludendorff";
} else if (Q.dnvp_line === 3 && Q.dnvp_candidate === Q.nsdap_candidate) {
    Q.dvfp_candidate = Q.nsdap_candidate;
} else {
    Q.dvfp_candidate = pickFreeCandidateFC("dvfp", Q.dvfp_default_candidate || "Graefe", [Q.dnvp_candidate, Q.nsdap_candidate]);
}

// --- DSBP — after DDP, DVP are final ----------------------------------------
if (Q.dsbp_votes > 0 && !Q.dsbp_banned) {
    var dsbp_crisis = Q.inflation < 0 || Q.unemployed >= 15;
    if (dsbp_crisis) {
        Q.dsbp_candidate = "Gessler";
    } else if (JOINT_LEFT) {
        Q.dsbp_candidate = (Q.ddp_candidate !== Q.kpd_candidate) ? (Q.ddp_candidate || Q.dvp_candidate || "Gessler") : (Q.dvp_candidate || "Gessler");
    } else if (Q.ddp_candidate && Q.dvp_candidate && Q.ddp_candidate === Q.dvp_candidate) {
        Q.dsbp_candidate = Q.ddp_candidate;
    } else {
        Q.dsbp_candidate = pickFreeCandidateFC("dsbp", Q.dsbp_default_candidate || "Gessler",
            [Q.ddp_candidate, Q.dvp_candidate, Q.spd_candidate]);
    }
}

// --- CSVD — previously never re-evaluated after SPD's choice at all.
//     Now gets the same live look every other centrist/agrarian party
//     gets, gated the same way the 1932+ override already gates it
//     (csvd_flee), so it only matters once CSVD is actually active.
if (Q.csvd_votes > 0 && !Q.csvd_banned) {
    Q.csvd_candidate = JOINT_LEFT
        ? (Q.csvd_default_candidate || "Lambach2")
        : pickFreeCandidateFC("csvd", Q.csvd_default_candidate || "Lambach2",
            [Q.z_candidate, Q.dnvp_candidate, Q.spd_candidate]);
}




// ========================================
// FORMERLY-MINOR PARTIES — now fully independent. Each is re-scored
// against its OWN bench default plus an offer list of already-finalized
// parties it would plausibly consider backing, exactly like every other
// independent party above. Gated by its own vote/ban check rather than
// a shared MINOR_GATES lookup.
// ========================================
if (Q.kpo_votes > 0 && !Q.kpo_banned) {
    Q.kpo_candidate = JOINT_LEFT
        ? Q.kpo_default_candidate
        : pickFreeCandidateFC("kpo", Q.kpo_default_candidate, [Q.kpd_candidate, Q.sapd_candidate]);
}
if (Q.sl_votes > 0 && !Q.sl_banned) {
    Q.sl_candidate = JOINT_LEFT
        ? Q.sl_default_candidate
        : pickFreeCandidateFC("sl", Q.sl_default_candidate, [Q.sapd_candidate, Q.spd_candidate]);
}
if (Q.aspd_votes > 0 && !Q.aspd_banned) {
    Q.aspd_candidate = JOINT_LEFT
        ? Q.aspd_default_candidate
        : pickFreeCandidateFC("aspd", Q.aspd_default_candidate, [Q.dvp_candidate, Q.spd_candidate]);
}
if (Q.vnr_votes > 0 && !Q.vnr_banned) {
    Q.vnr_candidate = JOINT_LEFT
        ? Q.vnr_default_candidate
        : pickFreeCandidateFC("vnr", Q.vnr_default_candidate, [Q.dvp_candidate, Q.nsdap_candidate]);
}
if (Q.hl_votes > 0 && !Q.hl_banned) {
    Q.hl_candidate = JOINT_LEFT
        ? Q.hl_default_candidate
        : pickFreeCandidateFC("hl", Q.hl_default_candidate, [Q.dhp_candidate, Q.cnbl_candidate]);
}
if (Q.lb_votes > 0 && !Q.lb_banned) {
    Q.lb_candidate = JOINT_LEFT
        ? Q.lb_default_candidate
        : pickFreeCandidateFC("lb", Q.lb_default_candidate, [Q.kpd_candidate, Q.sapd_candidate, Q.spd_candidate]);
}
if (Q.rdp_votes > 0 && !Q.rdp_banned) {
    Q.rdp_candidate = JOINT_LEFT
        ? Q.rdp_default_candidate
        : pickFreeCandidateFC("rdp", Q.rdp_default_candidate || "Quidde", [Q.ddp_candidate, Q.spd_candidate]);
}
if (Q.cvp_votes > 0 && !Q.cvp_banned) {
    Q.cvp_candidate = JOINT_LEFT
        ? Q.cvp_default_candidate
        : pickFreeCandidateFC("cvp", Q.cvp_default_candidate, [Q.z_candidate, Q.bvp_candidate, Q.spd_candidate]);
}
if (Q.sls_votes > 0 && !Q.sls_banned) {
    Q.sls_candidate = JOINT_LEFT
        ? Q.sls_default_candidate
        : pickFreeCandidateFC("sls", Q.sls_default_candidate, [Q.spd_candidate, Q.ddp_candidate, Q.z_candidate]);
}
if (Q.dtsp_votes > 0 && !Q.dtsp_banned) {
    Q.dtsp_candidate = Q.nsdap_banned
        ? (Q.dvfp_candidate || Q.dtsp_default_candidate || "Kunze")
        : pickFreeCandidateFC("dtsp", Q.dtsp_default_candidate || "Kunze", [Q.nsdap_candidate, Q.dvfp_candidate]);
}

// ========================================
// DNF — finalize
// ========================================
if (Q.dnf_banned) {
    Q.dnf_candidate = null;
} else if (Q.dnf_candidate) {
    // Already decided at arrival time, keep
} else if ((Q.dnf_line === 2 || Q.harzburg_front_seen) && !Q.nsdap_banned && Q.nsdap_candidate) {
    // Harzburg Front Alliance: Swallows pride to back the fascist candidate
    Q.dnf_candidate = Q.nsdap_candidate;
} else if (Q.dnf_line === 3 && Q.nsdap_r >= 33 && !Q.nsdap_banned && Q.nsdap_candidate) {
    // Kampffront Pragmatism: If the NSDAP is overwhelmingly dominant, avoid splitting the nationalist vote
    Q.dnf_candidate = Q.nsdap_candidate;
} else {
    // Line 1, minor lines, or running a independent bourgeois-nationalist spoiler ticket
    Q.dnf_candidate = "HugenbergDNF";
}


// ========================================
// 1932 HINDENBURG OVERRIDE — when active, Hindenburg becomes the
// default anti-extremist consensus pick for essentially every
// democratic/centrist/conservative party at once.
// ========================================
if (!Q.hindenburg_dead && Q.year >= 1932) {
    Q.hindenburg_running = 1;
    Q.hindenburg_candidate = "Hindenburg";

    if (Q.z_party_leader !== "Joos" || Q.z_relation < 35) { Q.z_candidate = "Hindenburg"; Q.z_default_candidate = "Hindenburg"; }
    Q.bvp_candidate = "Hindenburg"; Q.bvp_default_candidate = "Hindenburg";
    Q.dvp_candidate = "Hindenburg"; Q.dvp_default_candidate = "Hindenburg";
    Q.ddp_candidate = "Hindenburg"; Q.ddp_default_candidate = "Hindenburg";
    if (Q.dnvp_line !== 3) Q.dnvp_candidate = "Hindenburg";
    if (Q.wp_r > 2) { Q.wp_candidate = "Hindenburg"; Q.wp_default_candidate = "Hindenburg"; }
    if (Q.cnbl_r > 1.5) { Q.cnbl_candidate = "Hindenburg"; Q.cnbl_default_candidate = "Hindenburg"; }
    if (Q.csvd_flee === 1) { Q.csvd_candidate = "Hindenburg"; Q.csvd_default_candidate = "Hindenburg"; }
    if (Q.srpd_formed && Q.reformist_strength >= 30) Q.srpd_candidate = "Hindenburg";
    Q.csrp_candidate = "Hindenburg";
    Q.vrp_candidate = "Hindenburg"; Q.vrp_default_candidate = "Hindenburg";

    if (Q.dvfp_r > 0) {
        if (Q.dnvp_line === 3 && Q.dnvp_candidate !== "Hindenburg") { Q.dvfp_candidate = Q.dnvp_candidate; Q.dvfp_default_candidate = Q.dnvp_candidate; }
        else if (Q.nationalism >= 60 && Q.unrest_factor >= 2.5) { Q.dvfp_candidate = "Ludendorff"; Q.dvfp_default_candidate = "Ludendorff"; }
        else { Q.dvfp_candidate = "Hindenburg"; Q.dvfp_default_candidate = "Hindenburg"; }
    }
    if (Q.rdp_r > 0) Q.rdp_candidate = "Hindenburg";
    if (Q.cvp_r > 0) { Q.cvp_candidate = "Hindenburg"; Q.cvp_default_candidate = "Hindenburg"; }
    if (Q.sls_r > 0) Q.sls_candidate = "Hindenburg";
    if (Q.dtsp_r > 0) { Q.dtsp_candidate = Q.nsdap_candidate || Q.dvfp_candidate || "Kunze"; Q.dtsp_default_candidate = Q.dtsp_candidate; }
    if (Q.dsbp_r > 0 && !Q.dsbp_banned) { Q.dsbp_candidate = "Hindenburg"; Q.dsbp_default_candidate = "Hindenburg"; }
    if (Q.dbp_r > 0 && !Q.dbp_banned) {
        if (Q.dnvp_line === 3 && Q.rural_nsdap_support >= 25) { Q.dbp_candidate = "Fehr"; Q.dbp_default_candidate = "Fehr"; }
        else { Q.dbp_candidate = "Hindenburg"; Q.dbp_default_candidate = "Hindenburg"; }
    }
    // KPO/SL/ASPD/VNR/HL/LB are independent parties now: they are not
    // swept into the Hindenburg consensus automatically here. Each
    // already made its own free/finalist choice above via
    // pickFreeCandidateFC, backing Hindenburg only if its own scorer
    // judged that the best option (e.g. via KPD/SAPD/DVP/DHP already
    // having flipped to Hindenburg and being offered to them).
}

// Tactical/"stop the candidate I hate" consolidation deliberately does
// NOT happen here. This block only produces each party's SINCERE pick.
// Tactical awareness of projected standings runs later, in
// @tactical_consolidation, after the player's persuasion window closes
// — see that block for the full rationale.
Q.tactical_summary = ""; // cleared here; @tactical_consolidation sets it later if anyone defects

!}

