- @r1_menu: *Proceed to the first round of voting.*

@r1_menu
view-if: round = 0

Before the first round begins, we can try to convince other parties to change their support.

- @convince_z_unity: Try to convince the Center Party.
- @convince_ddp_unity: Try to convince the [+ ddp_name +].
- @convince_dvp_unity: Try to convince the DVP.
- @convince_kpd_spd: Try to convince the KPD.
- @round_1: Proceed to first round voting.

@convince_z_unity
title: Convince the Center Party to support [+ spd_candidate +].
view-if: z_candidate != spd_candidate and spd_candidate != kpd_candidate
max-visits: 1

- @pay_z: Offer resources (-2 resources).
- @r1_menu: Never mind.

@pay_z
choose-if: resources >= 2
subtitle: -2 resources
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources.
on-arrival: resources -= 2; z_candidate = spd_candidate; bvp_candidate = spd_candidate if bvp_candidate == z_candidate; Seldte_bonus += 2.5 if z_relation < 40;
go-to: r1_menu

With our resources, the Center is convinced to support [+ spd_candidate +].

@convince_ddp_unity
title: Convince the [+ ddp_name +] to support [+ spd_candidate +].
view-if: ddp_candidate != spd_candidate and spd_candidate != kpd_candidate
max-visits: 1
on-arrival: ddp_candidate = spd_candidate if ddp_relation >= 30;
go-to: r1_menu

[? if ddp_candidate == spd_candidate : The [+ ddp_name +] agrees to support [+ spd_candidate +]! ?]
[? if ddp_candidate != spd_candidate : The [+ ddp_name +] refuses to change their support. ?]

@convince_dvp_unity
title: Convince the DVP to support [+ spd_candidate +].
view-if: dvp_candidate != spd_candidate and spd_candidate != kpd_candidate
max-visits: 1
on-arrival: dvp_candidate = spd_candidate if dvp_relation >= 40;
go-to: r1_menu

[? if dvp_candidate == spd_candidate : The DVP agrees to support [+ spd_candidate +]! ?]
[? if dvp_candidate != spd_candidate : The DVP refuses to change their support. ?]

@convince_kpd_spd
title: Convince the KPD to support [+ spd_candidate +].
view-if: kpd_candidate != spd_candidate and spd_candidate != nsdap_candidate and spd_candidate != dnvp_candidate
choose-if: spd_votes >= kpd_votes
unavailable-subtitle: The KPD is more popular than us.
max-visits: 1

The KPD might be convinced to support [+ spd_candidate +].

- @kpd_resources: Use resources (-3 resources).
- @kpd_relations: Use our good relations.
- @r1_menu: Never mind.

@kpd_resources
view-if: kpd_relation >= 50
choose-if: resources >= 3
subtitle: -3 resources
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources.
on-arrival: resources -= 3; kpd_candidate = spd_candidate; sapd_candidate = spd_candidate;
go-to: r1_menu

The KPD now supports [+ spd_candidate +]!

@kpd_relations
view-if: kpd_relation >= 60 or (kpd_party_leader == "Conciliators" and kpd_relation >= 45)
unavailable-subtitle: Relations not good enough.
on-arrival: kpd_candidate = spd_candidate; sapd_candidate = spd_candidate;
go-to: r1_menu

The KPD now supports [+ spd_candidate +]!

@round_1
on-arrival: round = 1;
go-to: tactical_consolidation

@tactical_consolidation
on-arrival: {!

// =====================================================================
// PHASE 2 OF 2 — TACTICAL CONSOLIDATION ("stop the candidate I hate
// most" voting).
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
// Runs strictly AFTER every party's sincere pick is locked in
// (@resolve_ai_candidates) AND after the player's persuasion window
// (@r1_menu) has closed — so tactical defection reacts to the true
// final lineup, including any last-minute deals the player made, and
// sincere picks can never be contaminated by "what if I'm not viable"
// reasoning. Kept in its own block/scope on purpose: this function
// only ever asks "is my current pick viable, and if not, who do I
// switch to" — it never re-runs the ideology/home-bench scorer used to
// decide a party's SINCERE pick, so the two kinds of reasoning can't
// leak into each other.
//
// Symmetric by construction (same function call for every party, left
// or right). "Hostile" reuses the same relation<15 veto cliff used
// throughout the file. Runs multiple passes since one party's
// defection can shift projected standings enough to trigger another
// party's defection next pass (capped and damped so it settles rather
// than oscillating).
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------

var CAND_INFO_TC = {
    Hindenburg: { party: "I" }, Eckener: { party: "Unity" }, Gessler: { party: "Liberal" },
    Einstein: { party: "Independent" }, Mann: { party: "Independent" }, Ossietzky: { party: "Independent" },
    Hitler: { party: "NSDAP" }, Goring: { party: "NSDAP", aliases: ["Göring"] }, Goebbels: { party: "NSDAP" },
    Westarp: { party: "DNVP" }, Treviranus: { party: "DNVP" }, Lambach: { party: "DNVP" },
    Lindeiner: { party: "DNVP" }, Hugenberg: { party: "DNVP" }, Seldte: { party: "DNVP/Stahlhelm" },
    Adenauer: { party: "Z" }, Kaas: { party: "Z" }, Bruning: { party: "Z", aliases: ["Brüning"] },
    Schaffer: { party: "BVP", aliases: ["Schäffer"] }, Stresemann: { party: "DVP" }, Scholz: { party: "DVP" },
    Dingeldey: { party: "DVP" }, Curtius: { party: "DVP" }, Reinhold: { party: "DVP" },
    Heuss: { party: "DDP" }, Dietrich: { party: "DDP" }, Luders: { party: "DDP", aliases: ["Lüders"] },
    Lemmer: { party: "DDP" }, Mahraun: { party: "DStP/Jungdo" }, KochWeser: { party: "DStP", aliases: ["Koch-Weser"] },
    Maier: { party: "DStP" }, Thalmann: { party: "KPD", aliases: ["Thälmann"] }, Munzenberg: { party: "KPD", aliases: ["Münzenberg"] },
    Braun: { party: "SPD" }, Schumacher: { party: "SPD" }, Schmid: { party: "SPD (Reformist)" },
    Ollenhauer: { party: "SPD (Left)" }, Juchacz: { party: "SPD" }, Noske: { party: "SPD (Right)" },
    Rosenfeld: { party: "SAPD" }, Horsing: { party: "SRPD" }, Hamkens: { party: "CNBL" }, Behrens: { party: "CNBL" },
    Fehr: { party: "DBP" }, Drewitz: { party: "WP" }, Lambach2: { party: "CSVD" }, Graefe: { party: "DVFP" },
    Ludendorff: { party: "DVFP/Völkisch" }, Quidde: { party: "RDP" }, Bohm: { party: "VRP", aliases: ["Böhm"] },
    Kunze: { party: "DTSP" }, HugenbergDNF: { party: "DNF" }
};
var TC_ALIAS = {};
for (var tck in CAND_INFO_TC) {
    TC_ALIAS[tck] = tck;
    if (CAND_INFO_TC[tck].aliases) for (var tca = 0; tca < CAND_INFO_TC[tck].aliases.length; tca++) TC_ALIAS[CAND_INFO_TC[tck].aliases[tca]] = tck;
}
function tcCanon(name) {
    if (!name) return name;
    if (TC_ALIAS[name]) return TC_ALIAS[name];
    var stripped = name.normalize("NFD").replace(/[\u0300-\u036f]/g, "").replace(/_/g, "");
    return TC_ALIAS[stripped] || stripped;
}
function tcGetRelation(a, b) {
    if (!Q.party_relations || !Q.party_relations[a] || !Q.party_relations[a][b]) return 0;
    return Q.party_relations[a][b];
}
function tcCandDesc(name) {
    var key = tcCanon(name);
    var c = CAND_INFO_TC[key];
    return c ? (name + " (" + c.party + ")") : (name || "");
}

function tactical_projectStandings() {
    var votes = {};
    var ap = Q.parties;
    for (var i = 0; i < ap.length; i++) {
        var p = ap[i];
        var cand = Q[p + '_candidate'];
        if (!cand) continue;
        var key = tcCanon(cand);
        var pv = (Q[p + '_votes'] !== undefined && Q[p + '_votes'] !== null) ? Q[p + '_votes'] : (Q[p + '_r'] || 0);
        votes[key] = (votes[key] || 0) + pv;
    }
    var arr = [];
    for (var k in votes) arr.push({ name: k, votes: votes[k] });
    arr.sort(function (a, b) { return b.votes - a.votes; });
    return arr;
}

// A candidate counts as "in contention" if they're in the projected top
// three, or within TACTICAL_REACH of third place.
var TACTICAL_REACH = 3; // percentage points
function tactical_inContention(standings, candKey) {
    for (var i = 0; i < Math.min(3, standings.length); i++) {
        if (standings[i].name === candKey) return true;
    }
    var thirdVotes = standings.length > 2 ? standings[2].votes : 0;
    for (var i2 = 0; i2 < standings.length; i2++) {
        if (standings[i2].name === candKey) return (thirdVotes - standings[i2].votes) <= TACTICAL_REACH;
    }
    return false;
}

function tactical_isHostile(votingPartyKey, candidateName) {
    var fKey = tcCanon(candidateName);
    var c = CAND_INFO_TC[fKey];
    var candPartyLabel = c ? c.party : "";
    var relation = tcGetRelation(votingPartyKey.toUpperCase(), (candPartyLabel || "").toUpperCase());
    return relation < 15;
}

// Score used ONLY to rank in-contention alternatives against each
// other during tactical defection — not the sincere-pick scorer.
function tacticalOptionScore(votingPartyKey, candidateName) {
    var fKey = tcCanon(candidateName);
    var c = CAND_INFO_TC[fKey];
    var candPartyLabel = c ? c.party : "";
    var relation = tcGetRelation(votingPartyKey.toUpperCase(), (candPartyLabel || "").toUpperCase());
    var myIdeo = (Q[votingPartyKey + '_ideo_score'] !== undefined) ? Q[votingPartyKey + '_ideo_score'] : 5;
    var candIdeo = (Q[(candPartyLabel || "").toLowerCase().replace(/[^a-z]/g, "") + '_ideo_score'] !== undefined)
        ? Q[(candPartyLabel || "").toLowerCase().replace(/[^a-z]/g, "") + '_ideo_score'] : 5;
    var ideoGap = Math.abs(myIdeo - candIdeo);
    var vetoPenalty = (relation >= 15) ? 0 : (15 - relation) * 4;
    return -(ideoGap * 20) + (relation * 0.5) - vetoPenalty;
}

var TACTICAL_MAX_PASSES = 4;
var tactical_locked = {}; // parties that already defected once stay put (no flip-flopping pass to pass)
Q.tactical_switches = []; // for display/debugging: {party, from, to}

for (var pass = 0; pass < TACTICAL_MAX_PASSES; pass++) {
    var standings = tactical_projectStandings();
    if (!standings.length) break;
    var changedThisPass = false;

    for (var pi = 0; pi < Q.parties.length; pi++) {
        var party = Q.parties[pi];
        if (tactical_locked[party]) continue;
        var current = Q[party + '_candidate'];
        if (!current) continue;
        var currentKey = tcCanon(current);

        // Already backing a contender — nothing to reconsider.
        if (tactical_inContention(standings, currentKey)) continue;

        // Find the most hostile in-contention leader (worst score), and
        // the best in-contention alternative to consolidate behind.
        var worst = null, worstScore = Infinity;
        var best = null, bestScore = -Infinity;
        for (var si = 0; si < Math.min(3, standings.length); si++) {
            var contenderKey = standings[si].name;
            if (contenderKey === currentKey) continue;
            var s = tacticalOptionScore(party, contenderKey);
            if (s < worstScore) { worstScore = s; worst = contenderKey; }
            if (s > bestScore) { bestScore = s; best = contenderKey; }
        }
        if (!worst || !best || worst === best) continue;

        // Defect only if the leading contender we'd be blocking is a
        // genuine veto-tier hostile match, AND the alternative we'd
        // consolidate behind is NOT itself hostile (no point trading
        // one enemy for another).
        if (tactical_isHostile(party, worst) && !tactical_isHostile(party, best)) {
            Q.tactical_switches.push({ party: party, from: current, to: best });
            Q[party + '_candidate'] = best;
            tactical_locked[party] = true; // one defection per party per election; prevents oscillation
            changedThisPass = true;
        }
    }

    if (!changedThisPass) break;
}

// Human-readable summary for playtesting/tuning.
if (Q.tactical_switches.length) {
    var tsLines = [];
    for (var tsi = 0; tsi < Q.tactical_switches.length; tsi++) {
        var ts = Q.tactical_switches[tsi];
        tsLines.push(ts.party.toUpperCase() + " abandons " + tcCandDesc(ts.from) + " to stop a hostile front-runner, backing " + tcCandDesc(ts.to) + " instead");
    }
    Q.tactical_summary = tsLines.join("; ") + ".";
} else {
    Q.tactical_summary = "";
}

!}
go-to: post_r1

[? if tactical_summary : *Behind the scenes: [+ tactical_summary +]* ?]


@post_r1
on-arrival: {!

// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
// SHARED CANDIDATE LOOKUP — mirror of CANDIDATES (display info only).
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
var CAND_INFO = {
    Hindenburg: { name: "Paul von Hindenburg", party: "I" },
    Eckener:    { name: "Hugo Eckener",        party: "Unity" },
    Gessler:    { name: "Otto Gessler",        party: "Liberal" },
    Einstein:   { name: "Albert Einstein",     party: "Independent" },
    Mann:       { name: "Heinrich Mann",       party: "Independent" },
    Ossietzky:  { name: "Carl von Ossietzky",  party: "Independent" },
    Hitler:     { name: "Adolf Hitler",        party: "NSDAP" },
    Goring:     { name: "Hermann Göring",      party: "NSDAP", aliases: ["Göring"] },
    Goebbels:   { name: "Joseph Goebbels",     party: "NSDAP" },
    Westarp:    { name: "Kuno von Westarp",       party: "DNVP" },
    Treviranus: { name: "Gottfried Treviranus",   party: "DNVP" },
    Lambach:    { name: "Walter Lambach",         party: "DNVP" },
    Lindeiner:  { name: "Hans von Lindeiner-Wildau", party: "DNVP" },
    Hugenberg:  { name: "Alfred Hugenberg",       party: "DNVP" },
    Seldte:     { name: "Franz Seldte",           party: "DNVP/Stahlhelm" },
    Adenauer:   { name: "Konrad Adenauer",     party: "Z" },
    Kaas:       { name: "Ludwig Kaas",         party: "Z" },
    Bruning:    { name: "Heinrich Brüning",    party: "Z", aliases: ["Brüning"] },
    Schaffer:   { name: "Franz Schäffer",      party: "BVP", aliases: ["Schäffer"] },
    Stresemann: { name: "Gustav Stresemann",   party: "DVP" },
    Scholz:     { name: "Ernst Scholz",        party: "DVP" },
    Dingeldey:  { name: "Eduard Dingeldey",    party: "DVP" },
    Curtius:    { name: "Julius Curtius",      party: "DVP" },
    Reinhold:   { name: "Peter Reinhold",      party: "DVP" },
    Heuss:      { name: "Theodor Heuss",       party: "DDP" },
    Dietrich:   { name: "Hermann Dietrich",    party: "DDP" },
    Luders:     { name: "Hermann Lüders",      party: "DDP", aliases: ["Lüders"] },
    Lemmer:     { name: "Ernst Lemmer",        party: "DDP" },
    Mahraun:    { name: "Arthur Mahraun",      party: "DStP/Jungdo" },
    KochWeser:  { name: "Erich Koch-Weser",    party: "DStP", aliases: ["Koch-Weser"] },
    Maier:      { name: "Reinhold Maier",      party: "DStP" },
    Thalmann:   { name: "Ernst Thälmann",      party: "KPD", aliases: ["Thälmann"] },
    Munzenberg: { name: "Willi Münzenberg",    party: "KPD", aliases: ["Münzenberg"] },
    Braun:      { name: "Otto Braun",          party: "SPD" },
    Schumacher: { name: "Kurt Schumacher",     party: "SPD" },
    Schmid:     { name: "Carlo Schmid",        party: "SPD - R" },
    Ollenhauer: { name: "Erich Ollenhauer",    party: "SPD - L" },
    Juchacz:    { name: "Marie Juchacz",       party: "SPD" },
    Noske:      { name: "Gustav Noske",        party: "SPD - SC" },
    Rosenfeld:  { name: "Kurt Rosenfeld",      party: "SAPD" },
    Horsing:    { name: "Otto Hörsing",        party: "SRPD" },
    Hamkens:    { name: "Wilhelm Hamkens",     party: "CNBL" },
    Behrens:    { name: "Wilhelm Behrens",     party: "CNBL" },
    Fehr:       { name: "Anton Fehr",          party: "DBP" },
    Drewitz:    { name: "Max Drewitz",         party: "WP" },
    Lambach2:   { name: "Walther Lambach",     party: "CSVD" },
    Graefe:     { name: "Albrecht von Graefe", party: "DVFP" },
    Ludendorff: { name: "Erich Ludendorff",    party: "DVFP/Völkisch" },
    Quidde:     { name: "Ludwig Quidde",       party: "RDP" },
    Bohm:       { name: "Johannes Böhm",       party: "VRP", aliases: ["Böhm"] },
    Kunze:      { name: "Wilhelm Kunze",       party: "DTSP" },
    HugenbergDNF: { name: "Alfred Hugenberg",       party: "DNF", bloc: "far_right" }
};
var CAND_ALIAS = {};
for (var ck0 in CAND_INFO) {
    CAND_ALIAS[ck0] = ck0;
    if (CAND_INFO[ck0].aliases) for (var a0 = 0; a0 < CAND_INFO[ck0].aliases.length; a0++) CAND_ALIAS[CAND_INFO[ck0].aliases[a0]] = ck0;
}
function canon(name) {
    if (!name) return name;
    if (CAND_ALIAS[name]) return CAND_ALIAS[name];
    var stripped = name.normalize("NFD").replace(/[\u0300-\u036f]/g, "").replace(/_/g, "");
    return CAND_ALIAS[stripped] || stripped;
}
function candDesc(name) {
    var key = canon(name);
    var c = CAND_INFO[key];
    return c ? (c.name + " (" + c.party + ")") : (name || "");
}

// Reset "running" flags for everyone in the registry.
for (var k0 in CAND_INFO) Q[k0 + '_running'] = 0;

// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
// AGGREGATE VOTES — every party's vote share goes to its candidate
// (canonicalized so Lambach/Lambach_2/Lambach2 etc. never split a
// candidate's total across two buckets, which was a real bug before).
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
var candidate_votes = {};
var all_parties = Q.parties;

for (var i = 0; i < all_parties.length; i++) {
    var party = all_parties[i];
    var supported_candidate = Q[party + '_candidate'];
    if (!supported_candidate) continue;

    var key = canon(supported_candidate);
    Q[key + '_running'] = 1;

    var party_votes = (Q[party + '_votes'] !== undefined && Q[party + '_votes'] !== null) ? Q[party + '_votes'] : (Q[party + '_r'] || 0);
    candidate_votes[key] = (candidate_votes[key] || 0)
        + (Q.math_broken ? Q.impossible_add(0, party_votes) : party_votes);
}

// Apply per-candidate bonuses (e.g. Seldte_bonus from convince actions).
for (var k in candidate_votes) {
    if (Q[k + '_bonus']) {
        candidate_votes[k] += Q.math_broken ? Q.impossible_add(0, Q[k + '_bonus'] / 100) : (Q[k + '_bonus'] / 100);
    }
}

var total_votes = 0;
for (var k in candidate_votes) total_votes += candidate_votes[k];

// Build the sorted candidate list ONCE. All winner/runner-up/third and
// tie-break logic reads from this single deterministic ordering instead
// of a separate "> Q.winner_votes" scan (which was order-dependent on
// object key iteration and could silently flip winners on ties).
var candidates_array = [];
for (var k in candidate_votes) {
    var pct = Math.round(1000 * candidate_votes[k] / total_votes) / 10;
    Q[k + '_votes'] = pct;
    Q[k + '_votes_disp'] = pct.toFixed(1);
    candidates_array.push({ name: k, votes: candidate_votes[k], pct: pct });
}

// Sort by raw votes descending; ties broken by candidate key name so the
// result is reproducible and not dependent on insertion order.
candidates_array.sort(function (a, b) {
    if (b.votes !== a.votes) return b.votes - a.votes;
    return a.name < b.name ? -1 : (a.name > b.name ? 1 : 0);
});

Q.round1_winner = candidates_array.length ? candidates_array[0].name : null;
Q.round1_runner_up = candidates_array.length > 1 ? candidates_array[1].name : null;
Q.round1_winner_votes = candidates_array.length ? candidates_array[0].pct : 0;
Q.round1_runner_up_votes = candidates_array.length > 1 ? candidates_array[1].pct : 0;

Q.round1_third = candidates_array.length > 2 ? candidates_array[2].name : null;
Q.round1_third_votes = candidates_array.length > 2 ? candidates_array[2].pct : 0;
Q.round1_third_votes_disp = Q.round1_third_votes > 0 ? Q.round1_third_votes.toFixed(1) : "0.0";
Q.third_stays = Q.round1_third ? 1 : 0;
Q.round2_has_third = Q.third_stays;

Q.round1_winner_desc = candDesc(Q.round1_winner);
Q.round1_runner_up_desc = Q.round1_runner_up ? candDesc(Q.round1_runner_up) : "";
Q.round1_third_desc = Q.round1_third ? candDesc(Q.round1_third) : "";

Q.has_majority = (Q.round1_winner_votes >= 50) ? 1 : 0;

Q.winner = Q.round1_winner;
Q.winner_votes = Q.round1_winner_votes;
Q.winner_votes_disp = Q.winner_votes.toFixed(1);
Q.winner_desc = Q.round1_winner_desc;

Q.round1_all_candidates = [];
for (var i2 = 0; i2 < candidates_array.length; i2++) {
    Q.round1_all_candidates.push({
        name: candidates_array[i2].name,
        desc: candDesc(candidates_array[i2].name),
        votes: candidates_array[i2].pct.toFixed(1)
    });
}

if (Q.has_majority) {
    Q.president_history = Q.president_history || [];
    Q.president_history.push({
        name: Q.winner,
        desc: Q.winner_desc,
        year_start: Q.year,
        votes: Q.winner_votes_disp,
        runnerup: Q.round1_runner_up,
        runnerup_votes: Q.round1_runner_up_votes.toFixed(1),
        rounds: 1,
        all_candidates: Q.round1_all_candidates
    });
    Q.president_history_count = Q.president_history.length;
}

!}
go-to: r1_results

@r1_results
on-display: {!
var partyColors = {
    spd:"#E3000F", kpd:"#8B0000", sapd:"#C40000", srpd:"#FF6B6B",
    z:"#000000",   bvp:"#69A2BE", csrp:"#FFCCFF", ddp:"#DCCA4A",
    dvp:"#D5AC27", wp:"#424242",  cnbl:"#5D4E37", csvd:"#3f7bc1",
    dnvp:"#3f7bc1",nsdap:"#954B00",kvp:"#3f7bc1", dhp:"#5D4E37",
    bb:"#69A2BE",  vrp:"#8B7355", dvfp:"#7A5C12", other:"#a0a0a0",
    aspd:"#B22222", hl:"#2E8B57", sl:"#005B96", kpo:"#990000", vnr:"#4B5320",
    lb:"#6B0000", rdp:"#B8B000", cvp:"#1A1A1A", sls:"#4A7C59", dtsp:"#3B1A00", dbp: "#03A331", dsbp: "#7A9DB5", dnf: "#000F70"
};

var partyLabels = {
    spd:"SPD", kpd:"KPD", sapd:"SAPD", srpd:"SRPD", z:"Z", bvp:"BVP",
    csrp:"CSRP", ddp:Q.ddp_name||"DDP", dvp:"DVP", wp:"WP",
    cnbl:"CNBL", csvd:"CSVD", dnvp:"DNVP", nsdap:"NSDAP", kvp:"KVP",
    dhp:"DHP", bb:"BB", vrp:"VRP", dvfp:"DVFP", other:"Other",
    aspd:"ASPD", hl:"HL", sl:"SL", kpo:"KPO", vnr:"VNR",
    lb:"LB", rdp:"RDP", cvp:"CVP", sls:"SLS", dtsp:"DtsP", dbp:"DBP", dsbp: "DSBP", dnf: "DNF"
};

var allParties = Q.parties;

// Alias-aware canonicalization (self-contained per this block's own
// JS scope). Previously a bare accent-stripping canon2() with no
// alias table -- any candidate stored under an alias spelling could
// split into a duplicate row here instead of merging into one.
var CAND_ALIAS_DISPLAY = { "G\u00f6ring": "Goring", "Br\u00fcning": "Bruning", "Sch\u00e4ffer": "Schaffer",
    "L\u00fcders": "Luders", "Koch-Weser": "KochWeser", "Th\u00e4lmann": "Thalmann",
    "M\u00fcnzenberg": "Munzenberg", "B\u00f6hm": "Bohm" };
function canon2(name) {
    if (!name) return name;
    if (CAND_ALIAS_DISPLAY[name]) return CAND_ALIAS_DISPLAY[name];
    var stripped = name.normalize("NFD").replace(/[\u0300-\u036f]/g, "").replace(/_/g, "");
    return CAND_ALIAS_DISPLAY[stripped] || stripped;
}

var displayNames = {
    Thalmann:"Thälmann", Munzenberg:"Münzenberg", Bruning:"Brüning",
    Schaffer:"Schäffer", Goring:"Göring", KochWeser:"Koch-Weser", Lambach2:"Lambach (CSVD)"
};
function dname(k) { return displayNames[k] || k; }

var candidateTotals = {};
var grouped = {};

for (var i = 0; i < allParties.length; i++) {
    var p = allParties[i];
    var cand = Q[p + '_candidate'];
    if (!cand) continue;
    var candNorm = canon2(cand);
    var votes = (Q[p + '_votes'] !== undefined && Q[p + '_votes'] !== null) ? Q[p + '_votes'] : (Q[p + '_r'] || 0);
    if (votes <= 0) continue;
    if (!candidateTotals[candNorm]) candidateTotals[candNorm] = 0;
    candidateTotals[candNorm] += votes;
    if (!grouped[candNorm]) grouped[candNorm] = [];
    grouped[candNorm].push({ party: p, votes: votes });
}

var total = 0;
for (var k in candidateTotals) total += candidateTotals[k];

var candOrder = Object.keys(candidateTotals).sort(function(a,b){
    return candidateTotals[b] - candidateTotals[a];
});

var container = document.getElementById('pres_r1_chart');
if (!container) return;
container.innerHTML = "";
container.style.cssText = "width:100%; max-width:620px; font-family:sans-serif;";

var summaryHeader = document.createElement('div');
summaryHeader.style.cssText = "font-size:11px; font-weight:bold; color:#888; letter-spacing:0.08em;"
    + "text-transform:uppercase; margin-bottom:6px;";
summaryHeader.textContent = "First Round Results";
container.appendChild(summaryHeader);

var maxCandVotes = candidateTotals[candOrder[0]] || 1;

candOrder.forEach(function(cand) {
    var votes = candidateTotals[cand];
    var pct = total > 0 ? votes / total * 100 : 0;
    var barW = Math.round(votes / maxCandVotes * 100);

    var repParty = grouped[cand][0].party;
    var repColor = partyColors[repParty] || "#aaa";

    var row = document.createElement('div');
    row.style.cssText = "display:flex; align-items:center; gap:6px; margin-bottom:5px;";

    var nameEl = document.createElement('div');
    nameEl.style.cssText = "width:110px; font-size:12px; font-weight:bold; text-align:right;"
        + "flex-shrink:0; white-space:nowrap; overflow:hidden; text-overflow:ellipsis; color:#1a1a1a;";
    nameEl.textContent = dname(cand);

    var barWrap = document.createElement('div');
    barWrap.style.cssText = "flex:1; background:#e8e8e8; height:18px; border-radius:2px; position:relative;";

    var bar = document.createElement('div');
    bar.style.cssText = "height:100%; border-radius:2px; background:" + repColor
        + "; width:" + barW + "%; transition:width 0.3s;";

    var threshold = document.createElement('div');
    var thresholdPos = Math.min(100, Math.round(50 / (total > 0 ? candidateTotals[candOrder[0]] / total * 100 : 1) * 100));
    threshold.style.cssText = "position:absolute; top:0; left:" + thresholdPos + "%; width:2px; height:100%;"
        + "background:rgba(0,0,0,0.3); z-index:2;";

    var pctEl = document.createElement('div');
    pctEl.style.cssText = "width:42px; font-size:12px; color:#333; flex-shrink:0;";
    pctEl.textContent = pct.toFixed(1) + "%";

    barWrap.appendChild(bar);
    barWrap.appendChild(threshold);
    row.appendChild(nameEl);
    row.appendChild(barWrap);
    row.appendChild(pctEl);
    container.appendChild(row);
});

var legend = document.createElement('div');
legend.style.cssText = "font-size:11px; color:#888; margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:14px; padding-left:116px;";
legend.textContent = "▲ 50% majority threshold";
container.appendChild(legend);

var divider = document.createElement('div');
divider.style.cssText = "font-size:11px; font-weight:bold; color:#888; letter-spacing:0.08em;"
    + "text-transform:uppercase; border-top:1px solid #ddd; padding-top:8px; margin-bottom:6px;";
divider.textContent = "Party Support Breakdown";
container.appendChild(divider);

candOrder.forEach(function(cand) {
    if (!grouped[cand] || grouped[cand].length === 0) return;

    var candTotal = candidateTotals[cand];
    var candPct = total > 0 ? candTotal / total * 100 : 0;

    var candLabel = document.createElement('div');
    candLabel.style.cssText = "font-size:12px; font-weight:bold; color:#1a1a1a; margin-bottom:4px; margin-top:2px;";
    candLabel.textContent = dname(cand) + "  (" + candPct.toFixed(1) + "%)";
    container.appendChild(candLabel);

    var partiesIn = grouped[cand].slice().sort(function(a,b){return b.votes-a.votes;});
    var maxVotes = partiesIn[0].votes;

    partiesIn.forEach(function(item) {
        var row = document.createElement('div');
        row.style.cssText = "display:flex; align-items:center; gap:5px; margin-bottom:3px;";

        var chip = document.createElement('div');
        chip.style.cssText = "width:10px; height:10px; border-radius:2px; flex-shrink:0; background:"
            + (partyColors[item.party]||"#aaa") + ";";

        var nameEl = document.createElement('div');
        nameEl.style.cssText = "width:44px; font-size:11px; color:#333; flex-shrink:0; text-align:right;";
        nameEl.textContent = partyLabels[item.party] || item.party;

        var barWrap = document.createElement('div');
        barWrap.style.cssText = "flex:1; background:#f0f0f0; height:12px; border-radius:2px;";

        var bar = document.createElement('div');
        var barW = Math.round(item.votes / maxVotes * 100);
        bar.style.cssText = "height:100%; border-radius:2px; background:" + (partyColors[item.party]||"#aaa")
            + "; width:" + barW + "%; opacity:0.85;";

        var pctEl = document.createElement('div');
        pctEl.style.cssText = "width:36px; font-size:11px; color:#444; text-align:left; flex-shrink:0;";
        pctEl.textContent = item.votes.toFixed(1) + "%";

        barWrap.appendChild(bar);
        row.appendChild(chip);
        row.appendChild(nameEl);
        row.appendChild(barWrap);
        row.appendChild(pctEl);
        container.appendChild(row);
    });

    var spacer = document.createElement('div');
    spacer.style.cssText = "height:8px;";
    container.appendChild(spacer);
});

var winner = candOrder[0];
var winnerPct = total > 0 ? candidateTotals[winner] / total * 100 : 0;
var hasMajority = winnerPct >= 50;

var banner = document.createElement('div');
banner.style.cssText = "margin-top:4px; padding:6px 10px; border-radius:2px; font-size:12px; font-weight:bold;"
    + (hasMajority
        ? "background:#f0fff0; border-left:4px solid #2a7a2a; color:#1a1a1a;"
        : "background:#fff8f0; border-left:4px solid #c07000; color:#1a1a1a;");
banner.textContent = hasMajority
    ? "✓ " + dname(winner) + " wins with " + winnerPct.toFixed(1) + "% — majority achieved"
    : "⚠ No majority — " + dname(winner) + " leads with " + winnerPct.toFixed(1) + "% — runoff required";
container.appendChild(banner);
!}
go-to: election_end if has_majority; r2_start if not has_majority

**First Round Results:**

{!<div id="pres_r1_chart"></div>!}

@r2_start
on-arrival: {!

// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
// ROUND 2 CONSOLIDATION ENGINE
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
// This single function (consolidateRound2) replaces the old file's two
// independently-drifting copies of the same logic (one here, one each
// in push_third_resources and push_third_relations — the second of
// which referenced an undefined "finalists" variable and crashed).
// Because every block has its own JS scope in ChoiceScript, this
// function is intentionally short and self-contained so it can be
// safely re-declared verbatim wherever round 2 needs to re-consolidate
// (here, after pushing out third, and after switching SPD's support).
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------

// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
// RELATION/IDEOLOGY-DRIVEN CONSOLIDATION
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
// Which finalist a party's voters flock to is now driven by two real
// numbers instead of a hand-authored bloc-priority list per party:
//   1. candIdeoScore(candidate) - the candidate's party's 1-10 ideology
//      score (Q.<party>_ideo_score, computed once at game start from
//      the party's named ideology string via ideoScore()).
//   2. getRelationSafe(votingParty, finalistParty) - the live pairwise
//      relation from Q.party_relations, reflecting coalition history,
//      leader personality, bans, recent betrayals, etc.
// Ideology dominates (heavily weighted gap), relation breaks ties
// between similarly-distant finalists, and a hostile relation (<15)
// applies a steepening penalty rather than an absolute veto - a party
// can still "hold its nose" and back someone it despises if every
// other option is ideologically far worse.
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------

// Local candidate registry (party + bloc only, all this block needs).
// Previously missing entirely: candIdeoScore()/finalistScore() below
// referenced a bare `CANDIDATES` that was never defined in this block's
// scope, since ChoiceScript scopes JS per-block and @party_candidates's
// CANDIDATES table isn't visible here. That left ideology scoring
// silently broken (or erroring) for the entire round-2 runoff.
var CANDIDATES = {
    Hindenburg: { party: "I", bloc: "center" }, Eckener: { party: "Unity", bloc: "center_left" },
    Gessler: { party: "Liberal", bloc: "center_left" }, Einstein: { party: "Independent", bloc: "cultural" },
    Mann: { party: "Independent", bloc: "cultural" }, Ossietzky: { party: "Independent", bloc: "cultural" },
    Hitler: { party: "NSDAP", bloc: "far_right" }, Goring: { party: "NSDAP", bloc: "far_right" },
    Goebbels: { party: "NSDAP", bloc: "far_right" }, Westarp: { party: "DNVP", bloc: "center_right" },
    Treviranus: { party: "DNVP", bloc: "center_right" }, Lambach: { party: "DNVP", bloc: "center_right" },
    Lindeiner: { party: "DNVP", bloc: "center_right" }, Hugenberg: { party: "DNVP", bloc: "far_right" },
    HugenbergDNF: { party: "DNF", bloc: "far_right" }, Seldte: { party: "DNVP/Stahlhelm", bloc: "far_right" },
    Adenauer: { party: "Z", bloc: "center" }, Kaas: { party: "Z", bloc: "center" },
    Bruning: { party: "Z", bloc: "center" }, Schaffer: { party: "BVP", bloc: "center_right" },
    Stresemann: { party: "DVP", bloc: "center_left" }, Scholz: { party: "DVP", bloc: "center_right" },
    Dingeldey: { party: "DVP", bloc: "center_right" }, Curtius: { party: "DVP", bloc: "center" },
    Reinhold: { party: "DVP", bloc: "center_left" }, Heuss: { party: "DDP", bloc: "center_left" },
    Dietrich: { party: "DDP", bloc: "center_left" }, Luders: { party: "DDP", bloc: "center_left" },
    Lemmer: { party: "DDP", bloc: "center_left" }, Mahraun: { party: "DStP/Jungdo", bloc: "center_right" },
    KochWeser: { party: "DStP", bloc: "center_left" }, Maier: { party: "DStP", bloc: "center_left" },
    Thalmann: { party: "KPD", bloc: "far_left" }, Munzenberg: { party: "KPD", bloc: "far_left" },
    Braun: { party: "SPD", bloc: "left" }, Schumacher: { party: "SPD", bloc: "left" },
    Schmid: { party: "SPD (Reformist)", bloc: "center_left" }, Ollenhauer: { party: "SPD (Left)", bloc: "left" },
    Juchacz: { party: "SPD", bloc: "left" }, Noske: { party: "SPD (Right)", bloc: "center" },
    Rosenfeld: { party: "SAPD", bloc: "far_left" }, Horsing: { party: "SRPD", bloc: "center_left" },
    Hamkens: { party: "CNBL", bloc: "center_right" }, Behrens: { party: "CNBL", bloc: "center_right" },
    Fehr: { party: "DBP", bloc: "center" }, Drewitz: { party: "WP", bloc: "center_right" },
    Lambach2: { party: "CSVD", bloc: "center_right" }, Graefe: { party: "DVFP", bloc: "far_right" },
    Ludendorff: { party: "DVFP/Völkisch", bloc: "far_right" }, Quidde: { party: "RDP", bloc: "center_left" },
    Bohm: { party: "VRP", bloc: "center_right" }, Kunze: { party: "DTSP", bloc: "far_right" }
};
var CANDIDATES_ALIAS = { "Göring": "Goring", "Brüning": "Bruning", "Schäffer": "Schaffer",
    "Lüders": "Luders", "Koch-Weser": "KochWeser", "Thälmann": "Thalmann",
    "Münzenberg": "Munzenberg", "Böhm": "Bohm" };
function canon2(name) {
    if (!name) return name;
    if (CANDIDATES_ALIAS[name]) return CANDIDATES_ALIAS[name];
    var stripped = name.normalize("NFD").replace(/[\u0300-\u036f]/g, "").replace(/_/g, "");
    return CANDIDATES_ALIAS[stripped] || stripped;
}

// finalists is always derived fresh from current Q state, never assumed
// to exist from another block's scope (this is what fixes the crash).
function currentFinalists() {
    var f = [Q.round1_winner, Q.round1_runner_up];
    if (Q.round2_has_third && Q.round1_third) f.push(Q.round1_third);
    return f;
}

// Fallback ideology midpoints, used only when a candidate's party has
// no Q.<party>_ideo_score yet (independents, splinters not in Q.parties).
var BLOC_IDEO_FALLBACK = { far_left: 1, left: 2.5, cultural: 5, center_left: 4,
                            center: 5, center_right: 6.5, far_right: 9.5 };

function candIdeoScore(name) {
    var key = canon2(name);
    var c = CANDIDATES[key];
    if (!c) return 5;
    var partyKey = (c.party || "").toLowerCase().replace(/[^a-z]/g, "");
    if (Q[partyKey + '_ideo_score'] !== undefined) return Q[partyKey + '_ideo_score'];
    return (c.bloc && BLOC_IDEO_FALLBACK[c.bloc] !== undefined) ? BLOC_IDEO_FALLBACK[c.bloc] : 5;
}

function vetoPenalty(relation) {
    if (relation >= 15) return 0;
    return (15 - relation) * 4;
}

function finalistScore(votingPartyKey, finalist) {
    var fKey = canon2(finalist);
    var c = CANDIDATES[fKey];
    var finalistPartyLabel = c ? c.party : "";
    var relation = getRelationSafe(votingPartyKey.toUpperCase(), (finalistPartyLabel || "").toUpperCase());
    var myIdeo = (Q[votingPartyKey + '_ideo_score'] !== undefined) ? Q[votingPartyKey + '_ideo_score'] : 5;
    var ideoGap = Math.abs(myIdeo - candIdeoScore(finalist));
    return -(ideoGap * 20) + (relation * 0.5) - vetoPenalty(relation);
}

function pickBestFinalist(votingPartyKey, current_candidate) {
    var finalists = currentFinalists();
    var canonCurrent = canon2(current_candidate);
    for (var fi = 0; fi < finalists.length; fi++) {
        if (canon2(finalists[fi]) === canonCurrent) return current_candidate; // already a finalist
    }
    var best = finalists[0];
    var bestScore = finalistScore(votingPartyKey, finalists[0]);
    for (var f = 1; f < finalists.length; f++) {
        var s = finalistScore(votingPartyKey, finalists[f]);
        if (s > bestScore) { bestScore = s; best = finalists[f]; }
    }
    return best;
}

// Re-runs consolidation for every party. Safe to call multiple times
// (e.g. once at round-2 start, again after pushing out third, again
// after SPD switches support) since pickBestFinalist always reads
// live Q state and is a no-op for any party already on a finalist.
function consolidateRound2() {
    var finalists = currentFinalists();

    // Far-right NSDAP/DNVP mutual consolidation first (they often need
    // to agree with EACH OTHER before everyone else aligns to them).
    if (canon2(Q.nsdap_candidate) !== canon2(Q.dnvp_candidate)) {
        var nsdap_in = finalists.map(canon2).indexOf(canon2(Q.nsdap_candidate)) !== -1;
        var dnvp_in = finalists.map(canon2).indexOf(canon2(Q.dnvp_candidate)) !== -1;
        if (nsdap_in && !dnvp_in) {
            Q.dnvp_candidate = Q.nsdap_candidate;
        } else if (dnvp_in && !nsdap_in) {
            Q.nsdap_candidate = Q.dnvp_candidate;
        } else if (!nsdap_in && !dnvp_in) {
            var nsdap_votes = Q[canon2(Q.nsdap_candidate) + '_votes'] || 0;
            var dnvp_votes = Q[canon2(Q.dnvp_candidate) + '_votes'] || 0;
            var preferred = (nsdap_votes >= dnvp_votes) ? Q.nsdap_candidate : Q.dnvp_candidate;
            var landed = pickBestFinalist("nsdap", preferred);
            Q.nsdap_candidate = landed;
            Q.dnvp_candidate = landed;
        }
    }

    // Z's Kaas-vs-other leader split is already captured by the
    // Q.z_party_leader === "Kaas" term inside the Z->NSDAP relation
    // formula, so no hardcoded branch is needed here anymore.
    // SPD must also be consolidated: if the player's own candidate was
    // eliminated in round 1, Q.spd_candidate still points at them going
    // into round 2. Previously SPD was the only major party never run
    // through pickBestFinalist(), so an eliminated SPD candidate (e.g.
    // Braun) leaked into round-2 vote totals as a phantom extra
    // "third" bucket, which both inflated the denominator used for
    // Q.winner_votes and desynced it from the chart's own total
    // (which only sums the true finalist buckets) — the exact mismatch
    // between the results banner and the closing "elected with X%" line.
    if (Q.spd_candidate) Q.spd_candidate = pickBestFinalist("spd", Q.spd_candidate);
    if (Q.z_candidate) Q.z_candidate = pickBestFinalist("z", Q.z_candidate);
    if (Q.csrp_candidate) Q.csrp_candidate = pickBestFinalist("csrp", Q.csrp_candidate);
    if (Q.bvp_candidate) Q.bvp_candidate = pickBestFinalist("bvp", Q.bvp_candidate);
    if (Q.dvp_candidate) Q.dvp_candidate = pickBestFinalist("dvp", Q.dvp_candidate);
    if (Q.ddp_candidate) Q.ddp_candidate = pickBestFinalist("ddp", Q.ddp_candidate);
    if (Q.kpd_candidate) Q.kpd_candidate = pickBestFinalist("kpd", Q.kpd_candidate);
    if (Q.sapd_formed && Q.sapd_candidate) Q.sapd_candidate = pickBestFinalist("sapd", Q.sapd_candidate);
    if (Q.srpd_formed && Q.srpd_candidate) Q.srpd_candidate = pickBestFinalist("srpd", Q.srpd_candidate);
    if (Q.wp_candidate) Q.wp_candidate = pickBestFinalist("wp", Q.wp_candidate);
    if (Q.cnbl_candidate) Q.cnbl_candidate = pickBestFinalist("cnbl", Q.cnbl_candidate);
    if (Q.vrp_candidate) Q.vrp_candidate = pickBestFinalist("vrp", Q.vrp_candidate);
    if (Q.csvd_candidate) Q.csvd_candidate = pickBestFinalist("csvd", Q.csvd_candidate);
    if (Q.kvp_flee === 1 && Q.kvp_candidate) Q.kvp_candidate = pickBestFinalist("kvp", Q.kvp_candidate);
    if (Q.dhp_candidate) Q.dhp_candidate = pickBestFinalist("dhp", Q.dhp_candidate);
    if (Q.bb_candidate) Q.bb_candidate = pickBestFinalist("bb", Q.bb_candidate);
    if (Q.dvfp_candidate) Q.dvfp_candidate = pickBestFinalist("dvfp", Q.dvfp_candidate);
    if (Q.dbp_r > 0 && Q.dbp_candidate) Q.dbp_candidate = pickBestFinalist("dbp", Q.dbp_candidate);
    if (Q.dsbp_r > 0 && Q.dsbp_candidate) Q.dsbp_candidate = pickBestFinalist("dsbp", Q.dsbp_candidate);
    if (Q.dnf_votes > 0 && Q.dnf_candidate) Q.dnf_candidate = pickBestFinalist("dnf", Q.dnf_candidate);

    // Formerly-minor parties are independent now (own resolution/finalist
    // logic throughout), but Q.party_relations and *_ideo_score are still
    // only populated for the major party labels they historically split
    // from (KPD, SAPD, DVP, DHP, DDP, Z, SPD, NSDAP) — there is no
    // separate "KPO"/"SL"/etc. row in that external data. So the
    // relation/ideology lookup below still keys off that closest label,
    // purely so the round-2 scorer has real ideology data to compare
    // against instead of falling back to a flat neutral score; the
    // party's candidate selection itself is fully independent.
    if (Q.kpo_r > 0 && Q.kpo_candidate) Q.kpo_candidate = pickBestFinalist("kpd", Q.kpo_candidate);
    if (Q.sl_r > 0 && Q.sl_candidate) Q.sl_candidate = pickBestFinalist("sapd", Q.sl_candidate);
    if (Q.aspd_r > 0 && Q.aspd_candidate) Q.aspd_candidate = pickBestFinalist("dvp", Q.aspd_candidate);
    if (Q.vnr_r > 0 && Q.vnr_candidate) Q.vnr_candidate = pickBestFinalist("dvp", Q.vnr_candidate);
    if (Q.hl_r > 0 && Q.hl_candidate) Q.hl_candidate = pickBestFinalist("dhp", Q.hl_candidate);
    if (Q.lb_r > 0 && Q.lb_candidate) Q.lb_candidate = pickBestFinalist("kpd", Q.lb_candidate);
    if (Q.rdp_r > 0 && Q.rdp_candidate) Q.rdp_candidate = pickBestFinalist("ddp", Q.rdp_candidate);
    if (Q.cvp_r > 0 && Q.cvp_candidate) Q.cvp_candidate = pickBestFinalist("z", Q.cvp_candidate);
    if (Q.sls_r > 0 && Q.sls_candidate) Q.sls_candidate = pickBestFinalist("spd", Q.sls_candidate);
    if (Q.dtsp_r > 0 && Q.dtsp_candidate) Q.dtsp_candidate = pickBestFinalist("nsdap", Q.dtsp_candidate);

    // If third place was pushed out (round2_has_third just turned off),
    // anyone still pointing at them gets re-homed onto a real finalist.
    if (!Q.round2_has_third && Q.round1_third) {
        var parties_r2 = Q.parties;
        for (var i = 0; i < parties_r2.length; i++) {
            var p = parties_r2[i];
            var cand = Q[p + '_candidate'];
            if (!cand) continue;
            if (canon2(cand) === canon2(Q.round1_third)) {
                Q[p + '_candidate'] = pickBestFinalist(p, cand);
            }
        }
    }
}

consolidateRound2();

// Tactical/"stop the candidate I hate" defection deliberately does NOT
// run here. This block only produces each party's SINCERE runoff pick
// (own candidate if still a finalist, otherwise the ideologically
// nearest finalist). Tactical awareness of standings runs later, at
// @r2_vote, after the player's full round-2 negotiation window
// (push-out-third / switch-SPD / convince) has closed — see
// @tactical_consolidation_r2 for the full rationale.
Q.tactical_summary = "";

!}

**Second Round Runoff**

No candidate achieved a majority in the first round. The candidates advance to a runoff:

1. **[+ round1_winner_desc +]** - [+ round1_winner_votes +]%

2. **[+ round1_runner_up_desc +]** - [+ round1_runner_up_votes +]%

[? if round2_has_third : 3. **[+ round1_third_desc +]** - [+ round1_third_votes_disp +]% ?]

- @r2_menu: What should we do?

@r2_menu

[? if round2_has_third : Three candidates remain in the runoff: **[+ round1_winner +]** ([+ round1_winner_votes +]%), **[+ round1_runner_up +]** ([+ round1_runner_up_votes +]%), and **[+ round1_third +]** ([+ round1_third_votes_disp +]%). ?]
[? if not round2_has_third : Two candidates remain: **[+ round1_winner +]** ([+ round1_winner_votes +]%) and **[+ round1_runner_up +]** ([+ round1_runner_up_votes +]%). ?]

- @r2_push_out_third: Try to push out the third candidate.
- @r2_switch_spd: Change our own support.
- @r2_convince: Try to convince other parties.
- @r2_vote: Proceed to the final vote.

@r2_push_out_third
view-if: round2_has_third = 1
max-visits: 1

[+ round1_third_desc +] is still in the race with [+ round1_third_votes_disp +]%. We could try to convince them to withdraw.

- @push_third_resources: Spend resources to negotiate withdrawal (-2 resources).
- @push_third_relations: Use our political relationships (if relations are good enough).
- @r2_menu: Leave them in.

@push_third_resources
choose-if: resources >= 2
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources.
on-arrival: {!
    resources -= 2;
    Q.round2_has_third = 0;
    Q.third_stays = 0;
!}
go-to: r2_reconsolidate

@push_third_relations
view-if: (z_relation >= 60 and round1_third != "Thalmann" and round1_third != "Munzenberg" and round1_third != "Hitler" and round1_third != "Goring" and round1_third != "Goebbels") or (kpd_relation >= 65 and (round1_third = "Thalmann" or round1_third = "Munzenberg"))
unavailable-subtitle: Relations not strong enough to pressure a withdrawal.
on-arrival: {!
    Q.round2_has_third = 0;
    Q.third_stays = 0;
!}
go-to: r2_reconsolidate

@r2_reconsolidate
on-arrival: {!
// Re-declare the same compact consolidation logic used at r2_start.
// (ChoiceScript scopes JS per block, so this is intentionally the same
// short, crash-free function rather than relying on another block's
// scope — that mismatch is exactly what caused the original crash.)
// Driven by Q.<party>_ideo_score (ideology, dominant) and
// Q.party_relations (relation, tiebreaker + soft veto) instead of
// hardcoded bloc-priority lists — see consolidateRound2() above for
// the full rationale.
// Local candidate registry (party + bloc only). Same fix as r2_start:
// CANDIDATES was referenced below but never defined in this block's
// own scope, since ChoiceScript scopes JS per-block.
var CANDIDATES = {
    Hindenburg: { party: "I", bloc: "center" }, Eckener: { party: "Unity", bloc: "center_left" },
    Gessler: { party: "Liberal", bloc: "center_left" }, Einstein: { party: "Independent", bloc: "cultural" },
    Mann: { party: "Independent", bloc: "cultural" }, Ossietzky: { party: "Independent", bloc: "cultural" },
    Hitler: { party: "NSDAP", bloc: "far_right" }, Goring: { party: "NSDAP", bloc: "far_right" },
    Goebbels: { party: "NSDAP", bloc: "far_right" }, Westarp: { party: "DNVP", bloc: "center_right" },
    Treviranus: { party: "DNVP", bloc: "center_right" }, Lambach: { party: "DNVP", bloc: "center_right" },
    Lindeiner: { party: "DNVP", bloc: "center_right" }, Hugenberg: { party: "DNVP", bloc: "far_right" },
    HugenbergDNF: { party: "DNF", bloc: "far_right" }, Seldte: { party: "DNVP/Stahlhelm", bloc: "far_right" },
    Adenauer: { party: "Z", bloc: "center" }, Kaas: { party: "Z", bloc: "center" },
    Bruning: { party: "Z", bloc: "center" }, Schaffer: { party: "BVP", bloc: "center_right" },
    Stresemann: { party: "DVP", bloc: "center_left" }, Scholz: { party: "DVP", bloc: "center_right" },
    Dingeldey: { party: "DVP", bloc: "center_right" }, Curtius: { party: "DVP", bloc: "center" },
    Reinhold: { party: "DVP", bloc: "center_left" }, Heuss: { party: "DDP", bloc: "center_left" },
    Dietrich: { party: "DDP", bloc: "center_left" }, Luders: { party: "DDP", bloc: "center_left" },
    Lemmer: { party: "DDP", bloc: "center_left" }, Mahraun: { party: "DStP/Jungdo", bloc: "center_right" },
    KochWeser: { party: "DStP", bloc: "center_left" }, Maier: { party: "DStP", bloc: "center_left" },
    Thalmann: { party: "KPD", bloc: "far_left" }, Munzenberg: { party: "KPD", bloc: "far_left" },
    Braun: { party: "SPD", bloc: "left" }, Schumacher: { party: "SPD", bloc: "left" },
    Schmid: { party: "SPD (Reformist)", bloc: "center_left" }, Ollenhauer: { party: "SPD (Left)", bloc: "left" },
    Juchacz: { party: "SPD", bloc: "left" }, Noske: { party: "SPD (Right)", bloc: "center" },
    Rosenfeld: { party: "SAPD", bloc: "far_left" }, Horsing: { party: "SRPD", bloc: "center_left" },
    Hamkens: { party: "CNBL", bloc: "center_right" }, Behrens: { party: "CNBL", bloc: "center_right" },
    Fehr: { party: "DBP", bloc: "center" }, Drewitz: { party: "WP", bloc: "center_right" },
    Lambach2: { party: "CSVD", bloc: "center_right" }, Graefe: { party: "DVFP", bloc: "far_right" },
    Ludendorff: { party: "DVFP/Völkisch", bloc: "far_right" }, Quidde: { party: "RDP", bloc: "center_left" },
    Bohm: { party: "VRP", bloc: "center_right" }, Kunze: { party: "DTSP", bloc: "far_right" }
};
var CANDIDATES_ALIAS = { "Göring": "Goring", "Brüning": "Bruning", "Schäffer": "Schaffer",
    "Lüders": "Luders", "Koch-Weser": "KochWeser", "Thälmann": "Thalmann",
    "Münzenberg": "Munzenberg", "Böhm": "Bohm" };
function canon2(name) {
    if (!name) return name;
    if (CANDIDATES_ALIAS[name]) return CANDIDATES_ALIAS[name];
    var stripped = name.normalize("NFD").replace(/[\u0300-\u036f]/g, "").replace(/_/g, "");
    return CANDIDATES_ALIAS[stripped] || stripped;
}
function currentFinalists() { var f=[Q.round1_winner, Q.round1_runner_up]; if (Q.round2_has_third && Q.round1_third) f.push(Q.round1_third); return f; }
var BLOC_IDEO_FALLBACK = { far_left: 1, left: 2.5, cultural: 5, center_left: 4,
                            center: 5, center_right: 6.5, far_right: 9.5 };
function candIdeoScore(name) {
    var key = canon2(name);
    var c = CANDIDATES[key];
    if (!c) return 5;
    var partyKey = (c.party || "").toLowerCase().replace(/[^a-z]/g, "");
    if (Q[partyKey + '_ideo_score'] !== undefined) return Q[partyKey + '_ideo_score'];
    return (c.bloc && BLOC_IDEO_FALLBACK[c.bloc] !== undefined) ? BLOC_IDEO_FALLBACK[c.bloc] : 5;
}
function vetoPenalty(relation) { if (relation >= 15) return 0; return (15 - relation) * 4; }
function finalistScore(votingPartyKey, finalist) {
    var fKey = canon2(finalist);
    var c = CANDIDATES[fKey];
    var finalistPartyLabel = c ? c.party : "";
    var relation = getRelationSafe(votingPartyKey.toUpperCase(), (finalistPartyLabel || "").toUpperCase());
    var myIdeo = (Q[votingPartyKey + '_ideo_score'] !== undefined) ? Q[votingPartyKey + '_ideo_score'] : 5;
    var ideoGap = Math.abs(myIdeo - candIdeoScore(finalist));
    return -(ideoGap * 20) + (relation * 0.5) - vetoPenalty(relation);
}
function pickBestFinalist(votingPartyKey, current_candidate) {
    var finalists = currentFinalists();
    var cc = canon2(current_candidate);
    for (var fi=0; fi<finalists.length; fi++) if (canon2(finalists[fi]) === cc) return current_candidate;
    var best = finalists[0];
    var bestScore = finalistScore(votingPartyKey, finalists[0]);
    for (var f = 1; f < finalists.length; f++) {
        var s = finalistScore(votingPartyKey, finalists[f]);
        if (s > bestScore) { bestScore = s; best = finalists[f]; }
    }
    return best;
}
var parties_r2 = Q.parties;
for (var i = 0; i < parties_r2.length; i++) {
    var p = parties_r2[i];
    var cand = Q[p + '_candidate'];
    if (!cand) continue;
    if (canon2(cand) === canon2(Q.round1_third)) {
        Q[p + '_candidate'] = pickBestFinalist(p, cand);
    }
}
!}
go-to: r2_menu

[+ round1_third_desc +] has withdrawn from the race. Their supporters have consolidated around the remaining candidates.

@r2_switch_spd

We are currently supporting **[+ spd_candidate +]**.

[? if round2_has_third : Three candidates remain. We can support any of them. ?]
[? if not round2_has_third : Two candidates remain. ?]

This will cost one negotiating move, and other parties allied with us may follow.

- @switch_to_finalist1: Support [+ round1_winner +] ([+ round1_winner_votes +]%)
- @switch_to_finalist2: Support [+ round1_runner_up +] ([+ round1_runner_up_votes +]%)
- @switch_to_third: Support [+ round1_third +] ([+ round1_third_votes_disp +]%)
- @r2_menu: Keep current support.

@switch_to_finalist1
view-if: spd_candidate != round1_winner
choose-if: (round1_winner != "Hitler" and round1_winner != "Goring" and round1_winner != "Goebbels" and round1_winner != "Hugenberg" and round1_winner != "Seldte") or (kpd_relation >= 65 and (round1_winner = "Thalmann" or round1_winner = "Munzenberg"))
unavailable-subtitle: We cannot support this candidate.
on-arrival: {!
    Q.spd_candidate = Q.round1_winner;
    Q.is_unity_candidate = (Q.round1_winner !== "Thalmann" && Q.round1_winner !== "Munzenberg") ? 1 : 0;
    // Parties with strong SPD relations follow our switch immediately.
    if (Q.z_relation >= 50) Q.z_candidate = Q.spd_candidate;
    if (Q.dvp_relation >= 55) Q.dvp_candidate = Q.spd_candidate;
    if (Q.ddp_relation >= 50) Q.ddp_candidate = Q.spd_candidate;
!}
go-to: r2_menu

We now support [+ round1_winner +]. [? if z_relation >= 50 : The Center Party follows our lead. ?]

@switch_to_finalist2
view-if: spd_candidate != round1_runner_up
choose-if: (round1_runner_up != "Hitler" and round1_runner_up != "Goring" and round1_runner_up != "Goebbels" and round1_runner_up != "Hugenberg" and round1_runner_up != "Seldte") or (kpd_relation >= 65 and (round1_runner_up = "Thalmann" or round1_runner_up = "Munzenberg"))
unavailable-subtitle: We cannot support this candidate.
on-arrival: {!
    Q.spd_candidate = Q.round1_runner_up;
    Q.is_unity_candidate = (Q.round1_runner_up !== "Thalmann" && Q.round1_runner_up !== "Munzenberg") ? 1 : 0;
    if (Q.z_relation >= 50) Q.z_candidate = Q.spd_candidate;
    if (Q.dvp_relation >= 55) Q.dvp_candidate = Q.spd_candidate;
    if (Q.ddp_relation >= 50) Q.ddp_candidate = Q.spd_candidate;
!}
go-to: r2_menu

We now support [+ round1_runner_up +]. [? if z_relation >= 50 : The Center Party follows our lead. ?]

@switch_to_third
view-if: round2_has_third = 1 and spd_candidate != round1_third
choose-if: (round1_third != "Hitler" and round1_third != "Goring" and round1_third != "Goebbels" and round1_third != "Hugenberg" and round1_third != "Seldte") or (kpd_relation >= 65 and (round1_third = "Thalmann" or round1_third = "Munzenberg"))
unavailable-subtitle: We cannot support this candidate.
on-arrival: {!
    Q.spd_candidate = Q.round1_third;
    if (Q.z_relation >= 50) Q.z_candidate = Q.spd_candidate;
!}
go-to: r2_menu

We now support [+ round1_third +]. [? if z_relation >= 50 : The Center Party follows our lead. ?]

@r2_convince

- @convince_z_r2: Try to convince the Center Party.
- @convince_ddp_r2: Try to convince the [+ ddp_name +].
- @convince_dvp_r2: Try to convince the DVP.
- @convince_kpd_r2: Try to convince the KPD.
- @convince_csrp_r2: Try to convince the CSRP.
- @convince_dbp_r2: Try to convince the DBP.
- @r2_menu: Back.

@convince_csrp_r2
view-if: csrp_candidate != spd_candidate
on-arrival: csrp_candidate = spd_candidate if csrp_relation >= 40;
go-to: r2_convince

[? if csrp_candidate == spd_candidate : The CSRP now supports [+ spd_candidate +]! ?]
[? if csrp_candidate != spd_candidate : The CSRP refuses. ?]

@convince_dbp_r2
view-if: dbp_candidate != spd_candidate
on-arrival: dbp_candidate = spd_candidate if dbp_relation >= 50;
go-to: r2_convince

[? if dbp_candidate == spd_candidate : The DBP now supports [+ spd_candidate +]! ?]
[? if dbp_candidate != spd_candidate : The DBP refuses. ?]

@convince_z_r2
view-if: z_candidate != spd_candidate

- @pay_z_r2: Offer resources (-2 resources).
- @r2_convince: Back.

@pay_z_r2
choose-if: resources >= 2 and z_relation >= 35
subtitle: -2 resources
unavailable-subtitle: [? if resources < 2 : Not enough resources. ?][? if z_relation < 35 : Relations not good enough. ?]
on-arrival: resources -= 2; z_candidate = spd_candidate; bvp_candidate = spd_candidate if bvp_candidate == z_candidate;
go-to: r2_convince

The Center Party now supports [+ spd_candidate +]!

@convince_ddp_r2
view-if: ddp_candidate != spd_candidate
on-arrival: ddp_candidate = spd_candidate if ddp_relation >= 35;
go-to: r2_convince

[? if ddp_candidate == spd_candidate : The [+ ddp_name +] now supports [+ spd_candidate +]! ?]
[? if ddp_candidate != spd_candidate : The [+ ddp_name +] refuses. ?]

@convince_dvp_r2
view-if: dvp_candidate != spd_candidate
on-arrival: dvp_candidate = spd_candidate if dvp_relation >= 45;
go-to: r2_convince

[? if dvp_candidate == spd_candidate : The DVP now supports [+ spd_candidate +]! ?]
[? if dvp_candidate != spd_candidate : The DVP refuses. ?]

@convince_kpd_r2
view-if: kpd_candidate != spd_candidate
choose-if: kpd_relation >= 55
unavailable-subtitle: Relations not good enough.
on-arrival: kpd_candidate = spd_candidate; sapd_candidate = spd_candidate;
go-to: r2_convince

The KPD now supports [+ spd_candidate +]!

@r2_vote
on-arrival: round = 2;
go-to: tactical_consolidation_r2

@tactical_consolidation_r2
on-arrival: {!

// =====================================================================
// PHASE 2 OF 2 — TACTICAL CONSOLIDATION, ROUND 2.
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
// Same two-phase split as round 1: @r2_start (+ @r2_reconsolidate)
// produced each party's SINCERE runoff pick; the player's full
// negotiation window (push-out-third, switch-SPD, convince) has now
// closed; only now do parties re-check whether their current finalist
// is actually viable or whether they should tactically consolidate
// behind a less-hostile leader instead. Kept in its own block/scope so
// this reasoning never blends with the sincere pickBestFinalist() logic
// above it.
//
// With only 2-3 finalists in a runoff "in contention" is nearly always
// true, so this mostly matters for edge cases (e.g. a party still
// nominally attached to a withdrawn/pushed-out third candidate that
// slipped through, or a party whose sincere finalist pick is technically
// live but the OTHER two finalists are both viable and one is hostile).
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------

var CAND_INFO_TC2 = {
    Hindenburg: { party: "I" }, Eckener: { party: "Unity" }, Gessler: { party: "Liberal" },
    Einstein: { party: "Independent" }, Mann: { party: "Independent" }, Ossietzky: { party: "Independent" },
    Hitler: { party: "NSDAP" }, Goring: { party: "NSDAP", aliases: ["Göring"] }, Goebbels: { party: "NSDAP" },
    Westarp: { party: "DNVP" }, Treviranus: { party: "DNVP" }, Lambach: { party: "DNVP" },
    Lindeiner: { party: "DNVP" }, Hugenberg: { party: "DNVP" }, Seldte: { party: "DNVP/Stahlhelm" },
    Adenauer: { party: "Z" }, Kaas: { party: "Z" }, Bruning: { party: "Z", aliases: ["Brüning"] },
    Schaffer: { party: "BVP", aliases: ["Schäffer"] }, Stresemann: { party: "DVP" }, Scholz: { party: "DVP" },
    Dingeldey: { party: "DVP" }, Curtius: { party: "DVP" }, Reinhold: { party: "DVP" },
    Heuss: { party: "DDP" }, Dietrich: { party: "DDP" }, Luders: { party: "DDP", aliases: ["Lüders"] },
    Lemmer: { party: "DDP" }, Mahraun: { party: "DStP/Jungdo" }, KochWeser: { party: "DStP", aliases: ["Koch-Weser"] },
    Maier: { party: "DStP" }, Thalmann: { party: "KPD", aliases: ["Thälmann"] }, Munzenberg: { party: "KPD", aliases: ["Münzenberg"] },
    Braun: { party: "SPD" }, Schumacher: { party: "SPD" }, Schmid: { party: "SPD (Reformist)" },
    Ollenhauer: { party: "SPD (Left)" }, Juchacz: { party: "SPD" }, Noske: { party: "SPD (Right)" },
    Rosenfeld: { party: "SAPD" }, Horsing: { party: "SRPD" }, Hamkens: { party: "CNBL" }, Behrens: { party: "CNBL" },
    Fehr: { party: "DBP" }, Drewitz: { party: "WP" }, Lambach2: { party: "CSVD" }, Graefe: { party: "DVFP" },
    Ludendorff: { party: "DVFP/Völkisch" }, Quidde: { party: "RDP" }, Bohm: { party: "VRP", aliases: ["Böhm"] },
    Kunze: { party: "DTSP" }, HugenbergDNF: { party: "DNF" }
};
var TC2_ALIAS = {};
for (var tc2k in CAND_INFO_TC2) {
    TC2_ALIAS[tc2k] = tc2k;
    if (CAND_INFO_TC2[tc2k].aliases) for (var tc2a = 0; tc2a < CAND_INFO_TC2[tc2k].aliases.length; tc2a++) TC2_ALIAS[CAND_INFO_TC2[tc2k].aliases[tc2a]] = tc2k;
}
function tc2Canon(name) {
    if (!name) return name;
    if (TC2_ALIAS[name]) return TC2_ALIAS[name];
    var stripped = name.normalize("NFD").replace(/[\u0300-\u036f]/g, "").replace(/_/g, "");
    return TC2_ALIAS[stripped] || stripped;
}
function tc2GetRelation(a, b) {
    if (!Q.party_relations || !Q.party_relations[a] || !Q.party_relations[a][b]) return 0;
    return Q.party_relations[a][b];
}
function tc2CandDesc(name) {
    var key = tc2Canon(name);
    var c = CAND_INFO_TC2[key];
    return c ? (name + " (" + c.party + ")") : (name || "");
}
function tc2CurrentFinalists() {
    var f = [Q.round1_winner, Q.round1_runner_up];
    if (Q.round2_has_third && Q.round1_third) f.push(Q.round1_third);
    return f;
}
function tc2IsHostile(votingPartyKey, candidateName) {
    var fKey = tc2Canon(candidateName);
    var c = CAND_INFO_TC2[fKey];
    var candPartyLabel = c ? c.party : "";
    var relation = tc2GetRelation(votingPartyKey.toUpperCase(), (candPartyLabel || "").toUpperCase());
    return relation < 15;
}
function tc2Score(votingPartyKey, candidateName) {
    var fKey = tc2Canon(candidateName);
    var c = CAND_INFO_TC2[fKey];
    var candPartyLabel = c ? c.party : "";
    var relation = tc2GetRelation(votingPartyKey.toUpperCase(), (candPartyLabel || "").toUpperCase());
    var myIdeo = (Q[votingPartyKey + '_ideo_score'] !== undefined) ? Q[votingPartyKey + '_ideo_score'] : 5;
    var candIdeo = (Q[(candPartyLabel || "").toLowerCase().replace(/[^a-z]/g, "") + '_ideo_score'] !== undefined)
        ? Q[(candPartyLabel || "").toLowerCase().replace(/[^a-z]/g, "") + '_ideo_score'] : 5;
    var ideoGap = Math.abs(myIdeo - candIdeo);
    var vetoPenalty = (relation >= 15) ? 0 : (15 - relation) * 4;
    return -(ideoGap * 20) + (relation * 0.5) - vetoPenalty;
}

var finalists = tc2CurrentFinalists();
Q.tactical_switches = [];

for (var pi = 0; pi < Q.parties.length; pi++) {
    var party = Q.parties[pi];
    var current = Q[party + '_candidate'];
    if (!current) continue;
    var currentKey = tc2Canon(current);

    // Already backing a finalist — nothing to reconsider (this covers
    // the overwhelming majority of parties in a 2-3 candidate runoff).
    var alreadyFinalist = false;
    for (var fi = 0; fi < finalists.length; fi++) if (tc2Canon(finalists[fi]) === currentKey) { alreadyFinalist = true; break; }
    if (alreadyFinalist) continue;

    // Not on a finalist (e.g. stale pick from a withdrawn candidate that
    // slipped through). Find the most hostile finalist and the best
    // non-hostile alternative among the finalists.
    var worst = null, worstScore = Infinity;
    var best = null, bestScore = -Infinity;
    for (var si = 0; si < finalists.length; si++) {
        var s = tc2Score(party, finalists[si]);
        if (s < worstScore) { worstScore = s; worst = finalists[si]; }
        if (s > bestScore) { bestScore = s; best = finalists[si]; }
    }
    if (!worst || !best) continue;

    if (tc2IsHostile(party, worst) && !tc2IsHostile(party, best)) {
        Q.tactical_switches.push({ party: party, from: current, to: best });
    }
    // Regardless of hostility, a non-finalist pick must land on SOME
    // finalist for the vote tally to be coherent — default to best.
    Q[party + '_candidate'] = best;
}

if (Q.tactical_switches.length) {
    var ts2Lines = [];
    for (var ts2i = 0; ts2i < Q.tactical_switches.length; ts2i++) {
        var ts2 = Q.tactical_switches[ts2i];
        ts2Lines.push(ts2.party.toUpperCase() + " abandons " + tc2CandDesc(ts2.from) + " to stop a hostile front-runner, backing " + tc2CandDesc(ts2.to) + " instead");
    }
    Q.tactical_summary = ts2Lines.join("; ") + ".";
} else {
    Q.tactical_summary = "";
}

!}
go-to: post_r2

[? if tactical_summary : *Behind the scenes: [+ tactical_summary +]* ?]



@post_r2
on-arrival: {!

// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
// SHARED CANDIDATE LOOKUP — mirror of CANDIDATES (display info only).
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
var CAND_INFO = {
    Hindenburg: { name: "Paul von Hindenburg", party: "I" },
    Eckener:    { name: "Hugo Eckener",        party: "Unity" },
    Gessler:    { name: "Otto Gessler",        party: "Liberal" },
    Einstein:   { name: "Albert Einstein",     party: "Independent" },
    Mann:       { name: "Heinrich Mann",       party: "Independent" },
    Ossietzky:  { name: "Carl von Ossietzky",  party: "Independent" },
    Hitler:     { name: "Adolf Hitler",        party: "NSDAP" },
    Goring:     { name: "Hermann Göring",      party: "NSDAP", aliases: ["Göring"] },
    Goebbels:   { name: "Joseph Goebbels",     party: "NSDAP" },
    Westarp:    { name: "Kuno von Westarp",       party: "DNVP" },
    Treviranus: { name: "Gottfried Treviranus",   party: "DNVP" },
    Lambach:    { name: "Walter Lambach",         party: "DNVP" },
    Lindeiner:  { name: "Hans von Lindeiner-Wildau", party: "DNVP" },
    Hugenberg:  { name: "Alfred Hugenberg",       party: "DNVP" },
    Seldte:     { name: "Franz Seldte",           party: "DNVP/Stahlhelm" },
    Adenauer:   { name: "Konrad Adenauer",     party: "Z" },
    Kaas:       { name: "Ludwig Kaas",         party: "Z" },
    Bruning:    { name: "Heinrich Brüning",    party: "Z", aliases: ["Brüning"] },
    Schaffer:   { name: "Franz Schäffer",      party: "BVP", aliases: ["Schäffer"] },
    Stresemann: { name: "Gustav Stresemann",   party: "DVP" },
    Scholz:     { name: "Ernst Scholz",        party: "DVP" },
    Dingeldey:  { name: "Eduard Dingeldey",    party: "DVP" },
    Curtius:    { name: "Julius Curtius",      party: "DVP" },
    Reinhold:   { name: "Peter Reinhold",      party: "DVP" },
    Heuss:      { name: "Theodor Heuss",       party: "DDP" },
    Dietrich:   { name: "Hermann Dietrich",    party: "DDP" },
    Luders:     { name: "Hermann Lüders",      party: "DDP", aliases: ["Lüders"] },
    Lemmer:     { name: "Ernst Lemmer",        party: "DDP" },
    Mahraun:    { name: "Arthur Mahraun",      party: "DStP/Jungdo" },
    KochWeser:  { name: "Erich Koch-Weser",    party: "DStP", aliases: ["Koch-Weser"] },
    Maier:      { name: "Reinhold Maier",      party: "DStP" },
    Thalmann:   { name: "Ernst Thälmann",      party: "KPD", aliases: ["Thälmann"] },
    Munzenberg: { name: "Willi Münzenberg",    party: "KPD", aliases: ["Münzenberg"] },
    Braun:      { name: "Otto Braun",          party: "SPD" },
    Schumacher: { name: "Kurt Schumacher",     party: "SPD" },
    Schmid:     { name: "Carlo Schmid",        party: "SPD - R" },
    Ollenhauer: { name: "Erich Ollenhauer",    party: "SPD - L" },
    Juchacz:    { name: "Marie Juchacz",       party: "SPD" },
    Noske:      { name: "Gustav Noske",        party: "SPD - SC" },
    Rosenfeld:  { name: "Kurt Rosenfeld",      party: "SAPD" },
    Horsing:    { name: "Otto Hörsing",        party: "SRPD" },
    Hamkens:    { name: "Wilhelm Hamkens",     party: "CNBL" },
    Behrens:    { name: "Wilhelm Behrens",     party: "CNBL" },
    Fehr:       { name: "Anton Fehr",          party: "DBP" },
    Drewitz:    { name: "Max Drewitz",         party: "WP" },
    Lambach2:   { name: "Walther Lambach",     party: "CSVD" },
    Graefe:     { name: "Albrecht von Graefe", party: "DVFP" },
    Ludendorff: { name: "Erich Ludendorff",    party: "DVFP/Völkisch" },
    Quidde:     { name: "Ludwig Quidde",       party: "RDP" },
    Bohm:       { name: "Johannes Böhm",       party: "VRP", aliases: ["Böhm"] },
    Kunze:      { name: "Wilhelm Kunze",       party: "DTSP" },
    HugenbergDNF: { name: "Alfred Hugenberg",  party: "DNF" }
};
var CAND_ALIAS = {};
for (var ck0 in CAND_INFO) {
    CAND_ALIAS[ck0] = ck0;
    if (CAND_INFO[ck0].aliases) for (var a0 = 0; a0 < CAND_INFO[ck0].aliases.length; a0++) CAND_ALIAS[CAND_INFO[ck0].aliases[a0]] = ck0;
}
function canon(name) {
    if (!name) return name;
    if (CAND_ALIAS[name]) return CAND_ALIAS[name];
    var stripped = name.normalize("NFD").replace(/[\u0300-\u036f]/g, "").replace(/_/g, "");
    return CAND_ALIAS[stripped] || stripped;
}
function candDesc(name) {
    var key = canon(name);
    var c = CAND_INFO[key];
    return c ? (c.name + " (" + c.party + ")") : (name || "");
}

// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
// FINAL VOTE TALLY — same canon()-normalized aggregation and
// deterministic tie-break as @post_r1.
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
var candidate_votes = {};
var parties = Q.parties;

for (var i = 0; i < parties.length; i++) {
    var party = parties[i];
    var supported_candidate = Q[party + '_candidate'];
    if (!supported_candidate) continue;

    var key = canon(supported_candidate);
    var party_votes = (Q[party + '_votes'] !== undefined && Q[party + '_votes'] !== null) ? Q[party + '_votes'] : (Q[party + '_r'] || 0);
    candidate_votes[key] = (candidate_votes[key] || 0)
        + (Q.math_broken ? Q.impossible_add(0, party_votes) : party_votes);

    Q[party + '_r2_votes'] = party_votes;
}

for (var k in candidate_votes) {
    if (Q[k + '_bonus']) {
        candidate_votes[k] += Q.math_broken ? Q.impossible_add(0, Q[k + '_bonus'] / 100) : (Q[k + '_bonus'] / 100);
    }
}

var total_votes = 0;
for (var k in candidate_votes) total_votes += candidate_votes[k];

var candidates_array2 = [];
for (var k in candidate_votes) candidates_array2.push({ name: k, votes: candidate_votes[k] });
candidates_array2.sort(function (a, b) {
    if (b.votes !== a.votes) return b.votes - a.votes;
    return a.name < b.name ? -1 : (a.name > b.name ? 1 : 0);
});

Q.winner = candidates_array2.length ? candidates_array2[0].name : null;
Q.winner_votes = total_votes > 0 ? Math.round(1000 * candidates_array2[0].votes / total_votes) / 10 : 0;
Q.winner_votes_disp = Q.winner_votes.toFixed(1);

Q.runnerup = canon(Q.round1_winner) === Q.winner ? Q.round1_runner_up : Q.round1_winner;
var runnerupKey = canon(Q.runnerup);
var runnerupRaw = candidate_votes[runnerupKey] || 0;
Q.runnerup_votes = total_votes > 0 ? Math.round(1000 * runnerupRaw / total_votes) / 10 : 0;
Q.runnerup_votes_disp = Q.runnerup_votes.toFixed(1);

Q.winner_desc = candDesc(Q.winner);

!}
on-display: {!

var partyColors = {
    spd:"#E3000F", kpd:"#8B0000", sapd:"#C40000", srpd:"#FF6B6B",
    z:"#000000",   bvp:"#69A2BE", csrp:"#FFCCFF", ddp:"#DCCA4A",
    dvp:"#D5AC27", wp:"#424242",  cnbl:"#5D4E37", csvd:"#3f7bc1",
    dnvp:"#3f7bc1",nsdap:"#954B00",kvp:"#3f7bc1", dhp:"#5D4E37",
    bb:"#69A2BE",  vrp:"#8B7355", dvfp:"#7A5C12", other:"#a0a0a0",
    aspd:"#B22222", hl:"#2E8B57", sl:"#005B96", kpo:"#990000", vnr:"#4B5320",
    lb:"#6B0000", rdp:"#B8B000", cvp:"#1A1A1A", sls:"#4A7C59", dtsp:"#3B1A00", dbp: "#03A331", dsbp: "#7A9DB5"
};

var partyLabels = {};
for (var i = 0; i < Q.parties.length; i++) {
    var p = Q.parties[i];
    partyLabels[p] = p.toUpperCase();
}
partyLabels.ddp = Q.ddp_name || "DDP";
partyLabels.dtsp = "DtsP";
partyLabels.dsbp = Q.dsbp_name || "DSBP";

var allParties = Q.parties;

// Alias-aware canonicalization (self-contained per this block's own
// JS scope). Previously a bare accent-stripping canon2() with no
// alias table -- any candidate stored under an alias spelling could
// split into a duplicate row here instead of merging into one.
var CAND_ALIAS_DISPLAY = { "G\u00f6ring": "Goring", "Br\u00fcning": "Bruning", "Sch\u00e4ffer": "Schaffer",
    "L\u00fcders": "Luders", "Koch-Weser": "KochWeser", "Th\u00e4lmann": "Thalmann",
    "M\u00fcnzenberg": "Munzenberg", "B\u00f6hm": "Bohm" };
function canon2(name) {
    if (!name) return name;
    if (CAND_ALIAS_DISPLAY[name]) return CAND_ALIAS_DISPLAY[name];
    var stripped = name.normalize("NFD").replace(/[\u0300-\u036f]/g, "").replace(/_/g, "");
    return CAND_ALIAS_DISPLAY[stripped] || stripped;
}

var displayNames = {
    Thalmann:"Thälmann", Munzenberg:"Münzenberg", Bruning:"Brüning",
    Schaffer:"Schäffer", Goring:"Göring", KochWeser:"Koch-Weser", Lambach2:"Lambach (CSVD)"
};
function dname(k) { return displayNames[k] || k; }

var finalist1 = canon2(Q.round1_winner);
var finalist2 = canon2(Q.round1_runner_up);

var buckets = {};
buckets[finalist1] = [];
buckets[finalist2] = [];
var extraKeys = []; // every non-finalist bucket, first-seen order — replaces the overwritten thirdKey

for (var i = 0; i < allParties.length; i++) {
    var p = allParties[i];
    var cand = Q[p + '_candidate'];
    if (!cand) continue;
    var candNorm = canon2(cand);
    var votes = (Q[p + '_votes'] !== undefined && Q[p + '_votes'] !== null) ? Q[p + '_votes'] : (Q[p + '_r'] || 0);
    if (votes <= 0) continue;
    var bucket = candNorm === finalist1 ? finalist1
               : candNorm === finalist2 ? finalist2
               : candNorm;
    if (!buckets[bucket]) {
        buckets[bucket] = [];
        if (bucket !== finalist1 && bucket !== finalist2) extraKeys.push(bucket);
    }
    buckets[bucket].push({ party: p, votes: votes });
}

function sumBucket(b) { return b.reduce(function(s,x){return s+x.votes;},0); }

var cols = [finalist1, finalist2].concat(extraKeys);
var colTotals = cols.map(function(k){ return sumBucket(buckets[k]); });
var total = colTotals.reduce(function(s,v){ return s+v; }, 0);
var colPcts = colTotals.map(function(v){ return total>0 ? v/total*100 : 0; });

var container = document.getElementById('pres_r2_chart');
if (!container) return;
container.innerHTML = "";
container.style.cssText = "width:100%; max-width:620px; font-family:sans-serif;";

var headerRow = document.createElement('div');
headerRow.style.cssText = "display:flex; gap:4px; margin-bottom:4px;";
cols.forEach(function(k, idx) {
    var isWinner = (k === Q.winner);
    var h = document.createElement('div');
    h.style.cssText = "flex:" + colPcts[idx] + "; text-align:center; font-size:12px; font-weight:bold;"
        + "white-space:nowrap; overflow:hidden; text-overflow:ellipsis; padding:2px 0;"
        + (isWinner ? "color:#1a1a1a;" : "color:#666;");
    h.textContent = dname(k) + " — " + colPcts[idx].toFixed(1) + "%"
        + (isWinner ? " ★" : "");
    headerRow.appendChild(h);
});
container.appendChild(headerRow);

var barRow = document.createElement('div');
barRow.style.cssText = "display:flex; gap:4px; height:130px; align-items:flex-end; margin-bottom:16px;";
cols.forEach(function(k, colIdx) {
    var colWrap = document.createElement('div');
    colWrap.style.cssText = "flex:" + colPcts[colIdx] + "; display:flex; flex-direction:column;"
        + "height:100%; border-radius:3px; overflow:hidden;"
        + (Q.round2_has_third && k === canon2(Q.round1_third) ? "opacity:0.8; outline:2px dashed #aaa;" : "");

    var partiesIn = buckets[k].slice().sort(function(a,b){return b.votes-a.votes;});
    var colTotal = colTotals[colIdx];
    partiesIn.forEach(function(p) {
        var segPct = colTotal > 0 ? p.votes / colTotal * 100 : 0;
        var seg = document.createElement('div');
        seg.style.cssText = "flex:" + segPct + "; background:" + (partyColors[p.party]||"#aaa")
            + "; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; overflow:hidden; min-height:0;";
        seg.title = (partyLabels[p.party]||p.party) + ": " + p.votes.toFixed(1) + "%";
        if (segPct > 5) {
            var lbl = document.createElement('span');
            lbl.style.cssText = "font-size:10px; font-weight:bold; color:#fff;"
                + "text-shadow:0 0 2px #000,0 0 2px #000; white-space:nowrap; pointer-events:none;";
            lbl.textContent = (partyLabels[p.party]||p.party) + " " + p.votes.toFixed(1) + "%";
            seg.appendChild(lbl);
        }
        colWrap.appendChild(seg);
    });
    barRow.appendChild(colWrap);
});
container.appendChild(barRow);

var divider = document.createElement('div');
divider.style.cssText = "font-size:11px; font-weight:bold; color:#888; letter-spacing:0.08em;"
    + "text-transform:uppercase; border-top:1px solid #ddd; padding-top:8px; margin-bottom:6px;";
divider.textContent = "Party Support Breakdown";
container.appendChild(divider);

var grouped = {};
for (var i = 0; i < allParties.length; i++) {
    var p = allParties[i];
    var cand = Q[p + '_candidate'];
    if (!cand) continue;
    var candNorm = canon2(cand);
    var votes = (Q[p + '_votes'] !== undefined && Q[p + '_votes'] !== null) ? Q[p + '_votes'] : (Q[p + '_r'] || 0);
    if (votes <= 0) continue;
    if (!grouped[candNorm]) grouped[candNorm] = [];
    grouped[candNorm].push({ party: p, votes: votes, cand: candNorm });
}

var candOrder = Object.keys(grouped).sort(function(a, b) {
    var totalA = grouped[a].reduce(function(s, x) { return s + x.votes; }, 0);
    var totalB = grouped[b].reduce(function(s, x) { return s + x.votes; }, 0);
    return totalB - totalA;
});

candOrder.forEach(function(cand) {
    if (!grouped[cand] || grouped[cand].length === 0) return;

    var isWinner = (cand === Q.winner);
    var candTotal = grouped[cand].reduce(function(s,x){return s+x.votes;},0);
    var candPct = total > 0 ? candTotal / total * 100 : 0;

    var candHeader = document.createElement('div');
    candHeader.style.cssText = "display:flex; align-items:center; gap:6px; margin-bottom:4px; margin-top:2px;";

    var candLabel = document.createElement('div');
    candLabel.style.cssText = "font-size:12px; font-weight:bold; color:" + (isWinner?"#1a1a1a":"#555") + ";";
    candLabel.textContent = dname(cand) + (isWinner ? " ★" : "") + "  (" + candPct.toFixed(1) + "%)";

    candHeader.appendChild(candLabel);
    container.appendChild(candHeader);

    var partiesIn2 = grouped[cand].slice().sort(function(a,b){return b.votes-a.votes;});
    var maxVotes = partiesIn2[0].votes;

    partiesIn2.forEach(function(item) {
        var row = document.createElement('div');
        row.style.cssText = "display:flex; align-items:center; gap:5px; margin-bottom:3px;";

        var chip = document.createElement('div');
        chip.style.cssText = "width:10px; height:10px; border-radius:2px; flex-shrink:0; background:"
            + (partyColors[item.party]||"#aaa") + ";";

        var nameEl = document.createElement('div');
        nameEl.style.cssText = "width:44px; font-size:11px; color:#333; flex-shrink:0; text-align:right;";
        nameEl.textContent = partyLabels[item.party] || item.party;

        var barWrap = document.createElement('div');
        barWrap.style.cssText = "flex:1; background:#f0f0f0; height:12px; border-radius:2px; position:relative;";

        var bar = document.createElement('div');
        var barW = Math.round(item.votes / maxVotes * 100);
        bar.style.cssText = "height:100%; border-radius:2px; background:" + (partyColors[item.party]||"#aaa")
            + "; width:" + barW + "%; opacity:0.85;";

        var pctEl = document.createElement('div');
        pctEl.style.cssText = "width:36px; font-size:11px; color:#444; text-align:left; flex-shrink:0;";
        pctEl.textContent = item.votes.toFixed(1) + "%";

        barWrap.appendChild(bar);
        row.appendChild(chip);
        row.appendChild(nameEl);
        row.appendChild(barWrap);
        row.appendChild(pctEl);
        container.appendChild(row);
    });

    var spacer = document.createElement('div');
    spacer.style.cssText = "height:8px;";
    container.appendChild(spacer);
});

var banner = document.createElement('div');
banner.style.cssText = "margin-top:8px; padding:6px 10px; background:#f5f5f5; border-left:4px solid #333;"
    + "border-radius:2px; font-size:12px; color:#1a1a1a; font-weight:bold;";
banner.textContent = "✓ " + dname(Q.winner) + " elected with " + (Q.winner_votes_disp||"—") + "% of the vote";
container.appendChild(banner);
!}
go-to: election_end

**Final Results:**

{!<div id="pres_r2_chart"></div>!}

[+ winner_desc +] has won the presidency with [+ winner_votes_disp +]% of the vote!

@election_end
on-departure: {!
Q.presidential_election_active = 0;
Q.president_term_start = Q.year;
Q.president_term_ended = 0;

var next_year = Q.math_broken ? Math.round(Q.impossible_add(Q.year, 7)) : Q.year + 7;
var next_month = Q.month;
if (!next_month || next_month < 1 || next_month > 12) next_month = 3;
if (!next_year || next_year < Q.year + 1) next_year = Q.year + 7;

Q.next_presidential_election_year = next_year;
Q.next_presidential_election_month = next_month;
Q.last_presidential_election = Q.year;

if (!Q.has_majority) {
    Q.president_history = Q.president_history || [];
    Q.president_history.push({
        name: Q.winner,
        desc: Q.winner_desc,
        year_start: Q.year,
        votes: Q.winner_votes_disp,
        runnerup: Q.runnerup,
        runnerup_votes: Q.runnerup_votes_disp,
        third: Q.round1_third || null,
        third_desc: Q.round1_third_desc || null,
        third_votes: Q.round1_third_votes_disp || null,
        third_stayed: Q.round2_has_third ? 1 : 0,
        rounds: 2,
        round1_candidates: Q.round1_all_candidates
    });
    Q.president_history_count = Q.president_history.length;
}

// Q.winner is already the canonical registry key (e.g. "Thalmann", not
// "Thälmann") at this point because @post_r1/@post_r2 both normalize
// through canon(). We only convert to the accented display form here,
// once, for storytelling text — president_party lookups below always
// match on the canonical key so there is exactly one spelling to keep
// in sync, not two.
var display_name_map = {
    'Thalmann': 'Thälmann', 'Munzenberg': 'Münzenberg', 'Goring': 'Göring',
    'Bruning': 'Brüning', 'Schaffer': 'Schäffer'
};
var winnerKey = Q.winner; // canonical key, used for all matching below
Q.winner = display_name_map[winnerKey] || winnerKey; // display form for prose

Q.president = Q.winner;
Q.president_term_start = Q.year;
Q.presidential_election_active = 0;
Q.president_term_ended = 0;

// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
// PRESIDENT PARTY — single canonical-key lookup table. To add a new
// possible winner's party affiliation, add ONE entry here. (The old
// file kept ~10 separate arrays, several of which listed both the
// accented and unaccented spelling of the same person, which is no
// longer necessary since winnerKey is always canonical.)
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------
var WINNER_PARTY = {
    Braun:"SPD", Schumacher:"SPD", Juchacz:"SPD", Schmid:"SPD", Ollenhauer:"SPD", Noske:"SPD",
    Thalmann:"KPD", Munzenberg:"KPD",
    Hitler:"NSDAP", Goring:"NSDAP", Goebbels:"NSDAP",
    Seldte:"DNVP", Westarp:"DNVP", Treviranus:"DNVP", Lambach:"DNVP", Lindeiner:"DNVP", Hugenberg:"DNVP",
    Adenauer:"Z", Kaas:"Z", Bruning:"Z",
    Schaffer:"BVP",
    Stresemann:"DVP", Gessler:"Liberal", Scholz:"DVP", Dingeldey:"DVP", Curtius:"DVP", Reinhold:"DVP",
    Heuss:"DDP", Dietrich:"DDP", Luders:"DDP", Lemmer:"DDP", Mahraun:"DStP", KochWeser:"DStP", Maier:"DStP",
    Hindenburg:"I", Eckener:"Unity", Einstein:"Independent", Mann:"Independent", Ossietzky:"Independent",
    Graefe:"DVFP", Ludendorff:"DVFP",
    Quidde:"RDP", Fehr:"DBP", Bohm:"VRP", Kunze:"DTSP",
    Rosenfeld:"SAPD", Horsing:"SRPD", Drewitz:"WP",
    Hamkens:"CNBL", Behrens:"CNBL", Lambach2:"CSVD"
};
Q.president_party = WINNER_PARTY[winnerKey] || Q.president_party || "";

!}
on-arrival: tag_2_pred = 1; president_term_start = year; presidential_election_active = 0;
go-to: ollenhauer_victory if winner = "Ollenhauer"; dvfp_victory if winner = "Graefe" or winner = "Ludendorff"; hindenburg_victory if winner = "Hindenburg"; hitler_victory if winner = "Hitler" or winner = "Göring" or winner = "Goring" or winner = "Goebbels"; seldte_victory if winner = "Seldte"; thalmann_victory if winner = "Thälmann" or winner = "Thalmann"; munzenberg_victory if winner = "Münzenberg" or winner = "Munzenberg"; eckener_win if winner = "Eckener"; juchacz_win if winner = "Juchacz"; bundesrepublik_win if winner = "Schumacher" or winner = "Schmid" or winner = "Adenauer" or winner = "Lambach2"; nazis_lose if winner = "Braun" or winner = "Gessler" or winner = "Stresemann" or winner = "Westarp"; cultural_victory if winner = "Ossietzky" or winner = "Mann"; einstein_victory if winner = "Einstein"; z_victory if winner = "Kaas" or winner = "Brüning" or winner = "Bruning"; bvp_victory if winner = "Schäffer" or winner = "Schaffer"; sapd_victory if winner = "Rosenfeld"; wp_victory if winner = "Drewitz"; srpd_victory if winner = "Horsing"; cnbl_victory if winner = "Hamkens" or winner = "Behrens"; noske_win if winner = "Noske"; seldte_victory if winner = "Hugenberg" or winner = "HugenbergDNF"

[+ winner_desc +] is now President of Germany.

@noske_win
on-arrival: social_fascism_accepted = 1; dnvp_relation += 20; reichswehr_loyalth += 0.10; kpd_relation -= 30; left_dissent += 10; rfb_strength *= 1.20
achievement: noske_leader

Gustav Noske, formerly the Reichswehr minister, has won the presidency. Let's see what he can do. Be aware of communists. They always lurk.

@dvfp_victory
on-arrival: president_party = "DVFP"; nationalism += 25; nsdap_relation -= 10; dnvp_relation -= 10; democratization -= 3

[? if winner = "Ludendorff" : General Erich Ludendorff, the hero of the Great War and champion of the völkisch movement, has achieved the victory he was denied in 1925. ?]
[? if winner = "Graefe" : Albrecht von Graefe and the Völkisch Freedom Party have stunned the republic, bringing the radical racial-nationalist movement to the highest office. ?]

The "System" has been dealt a mortal blow. The new President speaks of a national spiritual renewal and the purging of "un-German" influences.

[? if nsdap_banned = 0 : The Nazis are jubilant, seeing this as the final precursor to their own total power, though Ludendorff has no intention of being Hitler's subordinate. ?]

[? if presidential_powers == 0 : With full presidential powers, the völkisch regime begins a rapid dismantling of the Weimar Constitution. ?]
[? if presidential_powers >= 1 : Our previous constitutional reforms act as a final barrier, forcing the new President to contend with a hostile Reichstag. ?]

- @game_over

@ollenhauer_victory
on-arrival: president_party = "SPD"; socialism += 5; kpd_relation *= 1.25; sapd_relation *= 1.50; workers_spd += 5

Erich Ollenhauer, supporter of the leftist - marxist orientation of our party, currently head of Saxony has won the election.

@hindenburg_victory
on-arrival: president_party = "I"; nationalism += 10; dnvp_relation += 5; hindenburg_patience -= 10; camarilla_strength += 10; judiciary_reform -= 2

Paul von Hindenburg, the aging field marshal, becomes President of Germany. The old military hero represents traditional conservative values.

[? if presidential_powers >= 1 : However, constitutional reforms limit his ability to rule by decree... ?]

[? if presidential_powers = 0 : With full presidential powers, Hindenburg rules as a conservative figurehead, heavily influenced by his DNVP backers. ?]

- @game_over

@cnbl_victory

CNBL has secured the win.

@srpd_victory

Otto Hörsing has achieved the victory. Republic shall survive once more.

@wp_victory

Economic party has achieved victory it has never dreamt of! Middle class will be represented under the leadership of the Drewitz! Hopefully crisis finally settles down of the middle class.

@hitler_victory
on-arrival: chancellor = "Hitler"; chancellor_party = "NSDAP"

The Nazis waste no time consolidating power. [? if president != "Hitler" : The new president immediately appoints Hitler as chancellor. ?][? if president = "Hitler" : Hitler appoints himself chancellor. ?]

[? if presidential_powers >= 1 : However, we have limited presidential powers through constitutional reform... ?][? if presidential_powers = 0 : With full presidential powers at his disposal, Hitler moves to reshape Germany. ?]

- @game_over

@seldte_victory
on-arrival: chancellor = "Seldte"; chancellor_party = "DNVP"; nationalism += 20

Franz Seldte, leader of the Stahlhelm, becomes President and immediately declares martial law.

[? if presidential_powers >= 1 : However, our constitutional reforms limit his ability to rule by decree... ?]

[? if presidential_powers = 0 : With full presidential powers at his disposal, Seldte establishes a military-backed authoritarian regime. He appoints himself Chancellor and begins dismantling democratic institutions. ?]

[? if nsdap_banned = 0 and hitler_deported = 0 : The NSDAP is furious - they expected Seldte to be their puppet, but the old Stahlhelm general has his own plans. Hitler is placed under house arrest. ?]

[? if nsdap_banned = 0 and hitler_deported = 1 : The NSDAP protests, but with Hitler in exile, they lack the strength to challenge Seldte's military regime. ?]

[? if nsdap_banned = 1 : With the Nazis already banned, Seldte consolidates a conservative-nationalist dictatorship without fascist competition. ?]

Germany enters an era of military authoritarianism under the old veterans of the Great War.

@thalmann_victory
go-to: thalmann_democrat if presidential_powers; thalmann_civil_war if not presidential_powers

@thalmann_civil_war
on-arrival: kpd_relation += 20

Thälmann moves to consolidate power. The far-right launches a coup attempt. Civil war looms...

- @game_over

@thalmann_democrat
on-arrival: kpd_relation += 10

Despite fears, Thälmann respects constitutional limits. Germany has a Communist president, but democracy endures.

- @game_over

@munzenberg_victory
achievement: rote_millionar
on-arrival: kpd_relation += 10

Willi Münzenberg becomes president. The "Red Millionaire" promises to respect democratic institutions.

- @game_over

@eckener_win
achievement: zeppelin_kapitan

Hugo Eckener, the Zeppelin captain, becomes president - a symbol of German technical achievement and republican unity.

- @game_over

@juchacz_win
achievement: wahlrechts

Historic! Marie Juchacz becomes the world's first elected female president!

- @game_over

@bundesrepublik_win
achievement: bundesrepublik
go-to: nazis_lose

A new era begins with [+ winner_desc +] as president.

@einstein_victory
achievement: republik_der_wissenschaft

Albert Einstein becomes president - science and reason triumph!

- @game_over

@cultural_victory

[+ winner_desc +] becomes president, representing Germany's cultural and intellectual achievements.

- @game_over

@z_victory

The Center Party's candidate becomes president, strengthening Catholic political power.

- @game_over

@bvp_victory

The Bavarian People's Party achieves a surprising victory, with regional interests now in the presidency.

- @game_over

@sapd_victory

The SAPD achieves an unexpected victory! The socialist split has paid off for them.

- @game_over

@nazis_lose

The Nazis have been defeated. The far-right coalition collapses into infighting and bankruptcy. Democracy survives another challenge.

- @game_over

@game_over
title: Back to usual
go-to: root

The presidential election concludes. Germany's future remains to be written...
